{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775879288914,"sessionID":"ses_28558a73bffe63pzmnHs6VtxMQ","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa7784f001cZBuidRh7pWcky","messageID":"msg_d7aa76e88001Nb7Cj8JNne97n8","sessionID":"ses_28558a73bffe63pzmnHs6VtxMQ","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879314270,"sessionID":"ses_28558a73bffe63pzmnHs6VtxMQ","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa7db45001NOxsTFpZ2pDyZ0","messageID":"msg_d7aa76e88001Nb7Cj8JNne97n8","sessionID":"ses_28558a73bffe63pzmnHs6VtxMQ","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-f8efbfb17b9840e4b9ce9c786afd8384","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# Delta Spec: AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta spec defines the HTTP client implementation for the AgentCube Python SDK, including control plane and data plane clients with connection pooling, session management, timeout configuration, and exception handling.\n\n## Module\n\n`sdk-python` — `agentcube` package\n\n## Requirements\n\n### R1: CodeInterpreterClient lifecycle\n\nThe system SHALL construct a client that either reuses `session_id` or creates a session via `ControlPlaneClient.create_session`, then initializes `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with header `x-agentcube-session-id`.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n\n**AC1.1: Context manager cleanup**\n- GIVEN `CodeInterpreterClient` is used as a context manager\n- WHEN the block exits (with or without exception)\n- THEN `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()`, which closes the data-plane session, deletes the control-plane session if `session_id` was set, and closes the control plane HTTP session\n\n**AC1.2: Data plane init failure after session create**\n- GIVEN `session_id` was not provided and `create_session` succeeded\n- WHEN `_init_data_plane()` raises\n- THEN the client SHALL log a warning, call `delete_session(session_id)`, set `session_id` to `None`, and re-raise\n\n**AC1.3: Router URL required**\n- GIVEN neither `router_url` nor environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set\n- WHEN `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__` runs\n- THEN it SHALL raise `ValueError` explaining that Router URL must be provided via argument or `ROUTER_URL`\n\n### R2: Code Interpreter operations\n\nThe system SHALL expose `execute_command`, `run_code`, `write_file`, `upload_file`, `download_file`, `list_files`, and `stop` delegating to the data plane client where applicable.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n\n**AC2.1: Command non-zero exit**\n- GIVEN `execute_command` receives a response with `exit_code != 0`\n- WHEN the response JSON is parsed\n- THEN the system SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` with `exit_code`, `stderr`, and `command`\n\n**AC2.2: Python code execution path**\n- GIVEN `language` is `python`, `py`, or `python3`\n- WHEN `run_code` runs\n- THEN the system SHALL write a timestamped `.py` file via `write_file` and execute `python3 <file>` through `execute_command`\n\n### R3: AgentRuntimeClient lifecycle\n\nThe system SHALL bootstrap or reuse `session_id` from the Agent Runtime invocation endpoint via `GET` on the base invocation URL, then `POST` JSON payloads with session header.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n\n**AC3.1: Context manager**\n- GIVEN `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as a context manager\n- WHEN the block exits\n- THEN `close()` SHALL close the underlying `requests.Session`\n\n**AC3.2: Bootstrap session id**\n- GIVEN `session_id` is not provided\n- WHEN the client initializes\n- THEN it SHALL `GET` `{router}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` and read header `x-agentcube-session-id`; if missing, raise `ValueError` with message `Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id`\n\n**AC3.3: Invoke without session**\n- GIVEN `session_id` is falsy\n- WHEN `invoke` is called\n- THEN it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n\n### R4: Control plane HTTP client\n\nThe system SHALL use `requests.Session` with connection pooling (`HTTPAdapter`) for Workload Manager calls.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n\n**AC4.1: Create session**\n- GIVEN `ControlPlaneClient.create_session(name, namespace, metadata=None, ttl=3600)`\n- WHEN the request succeeds\n- THEN the client SHALL `POST {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON body `{\"name\",\"namespace\",\"ttl\",\"metadata\"}` and return `data[\"sessionId\"]` or raise `ValueError` if absent\n\n**AC4.2: Delete session**\n- GIVEN `delete_session(session_id)`\n- WHEN the server returns 404\n- THEN the method SHALL return `True`; on other failures it SHALL log and return `False`\n\n**AC4.3: Workload Manager URL and auth**\n- GIVEN `workload_manager_url` and `auth_token` may be omitted\n- WHEN the client initializes\n- THEN `base_url` SHALL resolve from `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`; token SHALL resolve from `auth_token` or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` via `read_token_from_file`, and if present set `Authorization: Bearer {token}`\n\n### R5: Data plane HTTP client (Code Interpreter)\n\nThe system SHALL target Router-relative paths under `{base_url}` derived from `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{ns}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\")` unless `base_url` is passed explicitly.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n\n**AC5.1: Execute command**\n- WHEN `execute_command` posts to `api/execute`\n- THEN the body SHALL be JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` and read timeout SHALL be `timeout_value + 2.0` seconds when numeric (to avoid `ReadTimeout` before PicoD returns exit 124)\n\n**AC5.2: Files API**\n- WHEN `write_file` runs\n- THEN it SHALL `POST api/files` with base64 `content`, `path`, `mode` `\"0644\"`\n- WHEN `upload_file` runs\n- THEN it SHALL `POST` multipart to `api/files` with headers including `x-agentcube-session-id`\n\n### R6: Data plane HTTP client (Agent Runtime)\n\nThe system SHALL `POST` JSON to the invocation base URL with headers `x-agentcube-session-id` and `Content-Type: application/json`.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n\n**AC6.1: Invoke timeout tuple**\n- GIVEN `invoke(..., timeout=None)`\n- WHEN the request is sent\n- THEN `timeout` SHALL be `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` where `self.timeout` defaults to `120`\n\n### R7: Session header management\n\nThe system SHALL use lowercase header name `x-agentcube-session-id` for SDK Router requests.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n\n**AC7.1: Code Interpreter session header**\n- GIVEN `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is constructed\n- WHEN any `_request` or upload runs\n- THEN the session SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` (upload sets it explicitly on the multipart POST)\n\n### R8: Exception hierarchy\n\nThe system SHALL define `AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, and `DataPlaneError` in `agentcube.exceptions`.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n\n**AC8.1: Command failure**\n- GIVEN remote command returns non-zero exit code in JSON\n- WHEN `execute_command` processes the response\n- THEN it SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` (subclass of `AgentCubeError`)\n\n**AC8.2: SessionError / DataPlaneError usage**\n- GIVEN the current package sources under `agentcube/`\n- WHEN searching for `raise SessionError` / `raise DataPlaneError`\n- THEN these classes are defined for extension but not raised by the core client modules in the extracted tree (callers MAY rely on `ValueError`, `requests` exceptions, or `CommandExecutionError`)\n\n### R9: Timeout behavior\n\nThe system SHALL default control-plane and data-plane read timeouts to `120` seconds and connect timeout to `5.0` seconds unless overridden per call.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n\n**AC9.1: Per-call override for code execution**\n- GIVEN `execute_command(command, timeout=None)`\n- WHEN `timeout` is `None`\n- THEN the effective timeout value SHALL default to `self.timeout` (`120`) for constructing the PicoD timeout string and read-timeout buffer logic\n\n**AC9.2: AgentRuntimeClient constructor timeouts**\n- GIVEN `AgentRuntimeClient(..., timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)`\n- WHEN `invoke` is called without `timeout`\n- THEN read timeout SHALL be `120` (instance default)\n\n## Dependencies\n\n```toml\ndependencies = [\n    \"requests\",\n    \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",\n    \"cryptography\",\n]\n\nrequires-python = \">=3.10\"\n```\n\n## Public API\n\nThe package `agentcube` exports:\n- `CodeInterpreterClient`\n- `AgentRuntimeClient`\n\nInternal clients (not in root `__all__`):\n- `ControlPlaneClient`\n- `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`\n- `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n\n## Notes\n\n- No single `Configuration` class exists; configuration is distributed across individual clients\n- Connection pooling is configured via `HTTPAdapter` with `pool_connections=10` and `pool_maxsize=10`\n- Session headers use lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id`\n- Router handles JWT authentication on data plane; SDK does not set `Authorization` header for data plane requests\n- Control plane uses `Authorization: Bearer {token}` when token is available","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775879314262,"end":1775879314267}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775879314296,"sessionID":"ses_28558a73bffe63pzmnHs6VtxMQ","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa7db5d001UFTLy16CwaG4RM","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7aa76e88001Nb7Cj8JNne97n8","sessionID":"ses_28558a73bffe63pzmnHs6VtxMQ","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":23587,"input":6295,"output":2253,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":15039}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775879315380,"sessionID":"ses_28558a73bffe63pzmnHs6VtxMQ","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa7dfb1001SZa0nY3CS63KRU","messageID":"msg_d7aa7db91001LDITbcGnNC8Bbs","sessionID":"ses_28558a73bffe63pzmnHs6VtxMQ","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879316231,"sessionID":"ses_28558a73bffe63pzmnHs6VtxMQ","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa7e2da001BW2qDamfmKaXW4","messageID":"msg_d7aa7db91001LDITbcGnNC8Bbs","sessionID":"ses_28558a73bffe63pzmnHs6VtxMQ","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-d0d96f0c5d8f4df5bd0aad953fae0c75","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification: AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n2: \n3: ## AR Metadata\n4: - **AR ID**: AR-027\n5: - **Title**: SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n6: - **Module**: sdk-python\n7: - **Language**: Python\n8: - **Size**: M\n9: - **Status**: Implementation Required\n10: \n11: ## Purpose\n12: This delta specification defines implementation requirements for the `CodeInterpreterClient` class in the AgentCube Python SDK, focusing on session lifecycle management, code execution, file operations, and HTTP client interactions.\n13: \n14: ## Requirements\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterClient initialization with environment variable resolution\n17: The system SHALL resolve `workload_manager_url` from parameter or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` environment variable, resolve `router_url` from parameter or `ROUTER_URL` environment variable (required), and resolve `auth_token` from parameter or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`.\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: All parameters provided explicitly\n20: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(name=\"test\", namespace=\"dev\", ttl=1800, workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\", router_url=\"http://router:9000\", auth_token=\"custom-token\")` is called\n21: - **WHEN** initialization completes\n22: - **THEN** the client SHALL use the provided `workload_manager_url`, `router_url`, and `auth_token` values directly\n23: \n24: #### Scenario: Workload Manager URL from environment\n25: - **GIVEN** environment variable `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` is set to `http://wm-default:8080`\n26: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(router_url=\"http://router:9000\")` is called without `workload_manager_url`\n27: - **THEN** the client SHALL resolve `workload_manager_url` to `http://wm-default:8080`\n28: \n29: #### Scenario: Router URL missing required parameter\n30: - **GIVEN** neither `router_url` parameter nor `ROUTER_URL` environment variable is set\n31: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient()` is initialized\n32: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message containing \"Router URL must be provided\"\n33: \n34: #### Scenario: Auth token from Kubernetes service account\n35: - **GIVEN** `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` contains valid JWT token\n36: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient()` is called without `auth_token` parameter\n37: - **THEN** the client SHALL read and use the token from the file path via `read_token_from_file`\n38: \n39: #### Scenario: Service account token file missing\n40: - **GIVEN** `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` does not exist\n41: - **WHEN** `auth_token` is not provided and `read_token_from_file` is called\n42: - **THEN** the system SHALL return empty string and `auth_token` SHALL be set to `None` (no Authorization header will be set)\n43: \n44: ### Requirement: Session lifecycle with context manager support\n45: The system SHALL support context manager protocol via `__enter__` and `__exit__`, create session via control plane if `session_id` not provided, and cleanup resources on exit.\n46: \n47: #### Scenario: Context manager entry with existing session_id\n48: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(session_id=\"existing-session\")` is created\n49: - **WHEN** the client enters a context manager block via `with client:`\n50: - **THEN** `__enter__` SHALL return `self` without creating a new session\n51: \n52: #### Scenario: Context manager entry creates new session\n53: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient()` is created without `session_id`\n54: - **WHEN** the client enters a context manager block\n55: - **THEN** the system SHALL call `ControlPlaneClient.create_session()`, set `session_id` to returned value, initialize `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, and return `self`\n56: \n57: #### Scenario: Context manager normal exit\n58: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterClient` is used in a `with` block and `session_id` was created during entry\n59: - **WHEN** the block exits normally\n60: - **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()`, which closes data-plane client, deletes control-plane session via `ControlPlaneClient.delete_session()`, and closes control-plane HTTP session\n61: \n62: #### Scenario: Context manager exit with exception\n63: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterClient` is used in a `with` block and an exception occurs in the block\n64: - **WHEN** the block exits with exception\n65: - **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()` to clean up resources, then re-raise the exception with exception info passed to `__exit__`\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: Manual stop after context manager\n68: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterClient` has already exited its context manager and `stop()` was called\n69: - **WHEN** `stop()` is called again manually\n70: - **THEN** subsequent calls SHALL be idempotent and not raise errors\n71: \n72: ### Requirement: Data plane initialization failure handling\n73: The system SHALL handle data plane initialization failures by cleaning up created sessions before re-raising.\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Data plane init fails after session creation\n76: - **GIVEN** `session_id` was not provided and `ControlPlaneClient.create_session()` succeeded returning \"new-session-123\"\n77: - **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises an exception during initialization\n78: - **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning message, call `ControlPlaneClient.delete_session(\"new-session-123\")`, set `session_id` to `None`, and re-raise the original exception\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: Data plane init fails with existing session\n81: - **GIVEN** `session_id=\"existing-456\"` was provided to constructor\n82: - **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises an exception\n83: - **THEN** the client SHALL NOT attempt to delete the session (as it was not created by this client), but SHALL re-raise the exception\n84: \n85: ### Requirement: Command execution with timeout and error handling\n86: The system SHALL execute shell commands via data plane, parse JSON response, handle non-zero exit codes, and support custom timeouts.\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Successful command execution\n89: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is initialized and session is active\n90: - **WHEN** `execute_command(\"echo 'hello world'\")` is called with default timeout\n91: - **THEN** the system SHALL POST to `api/execute` with JSON `{\"command\": [\"echo\", \"hello world\"], \"timeout\": \"120s\"}`, wait for response, and return `stdout` from response JSON\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: Command with non-zero exit code\n94: - **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"ls /nonexistent\")` is called\n95: - **WHEN** the response JSON contains `exit_code: 1` and `stderr: \"No such file or directory\"`\n96: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError(exit_code=1, stderr=\"No such file or directory\", command=\"ls /nonexistent\")`\n97: \n98: #### Scenario: Custom timeout for command execution\n99: - **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"sleep 10\", timeout=30.0)` is called\n100: - **WHEN** the request is prepared\n101: - **THEN** the body SHALL include `timeout: \"30s\"` and the HTTP read timeout SHALL be `32.0` seconds (30 + 2.0 buffer)\n102: \n103: #### Scenario: Command timeout without custom override\n104: - **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"long-running-command\")` is called without timeout parameter\n105: - **WHEN** the default timeout is applied\n106: - **THEN** the body SHALL include `timeout: \"120s\"` (from `self.timeout`) and read timeout SHALL be `122.0` seconds\n107: \n108: #### Scenario: Command with list argument format\n109: - **GIVEN** `execute_command([\"ls\", \"-la\", \"/tmp\"])` is called with list of strings\n110: - **WHEN** the command is executed\n111: - **THEN** the data plane SHALL receive the list directly in the JSON body `{\"command\": [\"ls\", \"-la\", \"/tmp\"], \"timeout\": \"120s\"}`\n112: \n113: ### Requirement: Code execution with language-specific handling\n114: The system SHALL support `run_code()` for multiple languages with special handling for Python via file write and execute.\n115: \n116: #### Scenario: Python code execution\n117: - **GIVEN** `run_code(language=\"python\", code=\"print('hello')\")` is called\n118: - **WHEN** the method executes\n119: - **THEN** the system SHALL generate timestamped filename (e.g., `code_20250411_123456.py`), call `write_file(content=\"print('hello')\", remote_path=\"<filename>\")`, then call `execute_command(f\"python3 {filename}\")` and return result\n120: \n121: #### Scenario: Python code with alternative language identifier\n122: - **GIVEN** `run_code(language=\"py\", code=\"x = 1 + 2; print(x)\")` is called\n123: - **WHEN** language is detected as Python variant\n124: - **THEN** the system SHALL use the same file-write-and-execute pattern as `\"python\"` or `\"python3\"`\n125: \n126: #### Scenario: Non-Python code execution\n127: - **GIVEN** `run_code(language=\"bash\", code=\"echo 'hello from bash'\")` is called\n128: - **WHEN** the language is not a Python variant\n129: - **THEN** the system SHALL POST directly to data plane `run_code` endpoint with `{\"language\": \"bash\", \"code\": \"echo 'hello from bash'\"}` body\n130: \n131: ### Requirement: File operations via data plane\n132: The system SHALL support write, upload, download, and list file operations with proper encoding and headers.\n133: \n134: #### Scenario: Write file with base64 encoding\n135: - **GIVEN** `write_file(content=\"hello world\", remote_path=\"/tmp/test.txt\")` is called\n136: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n137: - **THEN** the system SHALL POST to `api/files` with JSON `{\"content\": \"<base64>\", \"path\": \"/tmp/test.txt\", \"mode\": \"0644\"}` where content is base64-encoded\n138: \n139: #### Scenario: Upload file via multipart\n140: - **GIVEN** `upload_file(local_path=\"/local/file.txt\", remote_path=\"/remote/file.txt\")` is called\n141: - **WHEN** the multipart request is sent\n142: - **THEN** the system SHALL POST to `api/files` with `files={'file': open('/local/file.txt', 'rb')}`, `data={'path': '/remote/file.txt', 'mode': '0644'}`, and header `x-agentcube-session-id: <session_id>`\n143: \n144: #### Scenario: Download file with streaming\n145: - **GIVEN** `download_file(remote_path=\"/data/result.json\", local_path=\"./result.json\")` is called\n146: - **WHEN** the file is downloaded\n147: - **THEN** the system SHALL GET `api/files/data/result.json` (cleaned path) with `stream=True`, write response content to `./result.json`, and close response after writing\n148: \n149: #### Scenario: List files in directory\n150: - **GIVEN** `list_files(path=\"/home/user\")` is called\n151: - **WHEN** the request completes\n152: - **THEN** the system SHALL GET `api/files?path=/home/user` and return the JSON response (typically file listing)\n153: \n154: #### Scenario: List files default path\n155: - **GIVEN** `list_files()` is called without path argument\n156: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n157: - **THEN** the system SHALL use default path `.` and query `api/files?path=.`\n158: \n159: ### Requirement: HTTP session management and connection pooling\n160: The system SHALL use `requests.Session` with `HTTPAdapter` for connection pooling on control plane and data plane clients.\n161: \n162: #### Scenario: Create session with default pool settings\n163: - **GIVEN** `create_session()` is called without arguments\n164: - **WHEN** the session is created\n165: - **THEN** the system SHALL create `requests.Session`, mount `HTTPAdapter` with `pool_connections=10` and `pool_maxsize=10` for both `http://` and `https://`, and return the session\n166: \n167: #### Scenario: Control plane client with custom pool settings\n168: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(pool_connections=20, pool_maxsize=20)` is initialized\n169: - **WHEN** the HTTP session is created\n170: - **THEN** the system SHALL use the custom pool values when calling `create_session()`\n171: \n172: #### Scenario: Data plane client uses provided session\n173: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is constructed with all required parameters\n174: - **WHEN** initialization completes\n175: - **THEN** the client SHALL create its own HTTP session via `create_session()` with configured pool settings\n176: \n177: #### Scenario: Closing sessions\n178: - **GIVEN** a client has an active `requests.Session`\n179: - **WHEN** `close()` is called\n180: - **THEN** the system SHALL call `self.session.close()` to properly close the session and release connections\n181: \n182: ### Requirement: Logger configuration\n183: The system SHALL configure logging with `get_logger()` utility supporting name and level parameters.\n184: \n185: #### Scenario: Logger with default INFO level\n186: - **GIVEN** `get_logger(\"agentcube.code_interpreter\")` is called\n187: - **WHEN** the logger is created\n188: - **THEN** the system SHALL return a `logging.Logger` instance with name `\"agentcube.code_interpreter\"` and level `logging.INFO`\n189: \n190: #### Scenario: Logger with custom level\n191: - **GIVEN** `get_logger(\"agentcube.client\", level=logging.DEBUG)` is called\n192: - **WHEN** the logger is created\n193: - **THEN** the system SHALL return a logger with level set to `logging.DEBUG`\n194: \n195: #### Scenario: Client initialization sets logger\n196: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(verbose=True)` is initialized\n197: - **WHEN** the logger is set\n198: - **THEN** the client SHALL create logger with level based on `verbose` flag (DEBUG if True, INFO if False)\n199: \n200: ### Requirement: Session header injection for data plane requests\n201: The system SHALL inject `x-agentcube-session-id` header into all data plane requests.\n202: \n203: #### Scenario: Request includes session header\n204: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(session_id=\"session-abc\")` is initialized\n205: - **WHEN** any `_request()` method call is made\n206: - **THEN** the request headers SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: session-abc`\n207: \n208: #### Scenario: Multipart upload includes session header\n209: - **GIVEN** `upload_file()` is called\n210: - **WHEN** the multipart POST is prepared\n211: - **THEN** the request SHALL explicitly set `x-agentcube-session-id` header alongside the multipart files and data\n212: \n213: #### Scenario: JSON request includes session header\n214: - **GIVEN** `execute_command()` is called with a JSON body\n215: - **WHEN** the POST request is sent\n216: - **THEN** the request SHALL include both `Content-Type: application/json` and `x-agentcube-session-id: <session_id>` headers\n217: \n218: ### Requirement: Base URL construction for data plane\n219: The system SHALL construct data plane base URL from router URL, namespace, and CR name unless explicitly provided.\n220: \n221: #### Scenario: Base URL from router and metadata\n222: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(router_url=\"http://router:9000\", namespace=\"default\", cr_name=\"my-interpreter\")` is initialized without `base_url`\n223: - **WHEN** the base URL is constructed\n224: - **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `http://router:9000/v1/namespaces/default/code-interpreters/my-interpreter/invocations/`\n225: \n226: #### Scenario: Explicit base URL overrides construction\n227: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(base_url=\"http://custom:8080/custom/path/\")` is provided\n228: - **WHEN** initialization completes\n229: - **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `http://custom:8080/custom/path/` without any router-based construction\n230: \n231: ### Requirement: Control plane session creation and deletion\n232: The system SHALL create sessions via POST to control plane API and delete via DELETE with 404 tolerance.\n233: \n234: #### Scenario: Create session returns session ID\n235: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(base_url=\"http://wm:8080\")` is initialized\n236: - **WHEN** `create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"dev\", ttl=1800, metadata={\"key\": \"value\"})` is called\n237: - **THEN** the system SHALL POST `http://wm:8080/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON body containing all parameters and return the `sessionId` from response\n238: \n239: #### Scenario: Create session missing session ID in response\n240: - **GIVEN** the control plane POST succeeds but response JSON lacks `sessionId` field\n241: - **WHEN** the response is parsed\n242: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating missing `sessionId`\n243: \n244: #### Scenario: Delete session success\n245: - **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session-123\")` is called and server returns 200 or 204\n246: - **WHEN** the response is processed\n247: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`\n248: \n249: #### Scenario: Delete session 404 treated as success\n250: - **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session-404\")` is called and server returns 404\n251: - **WHEN** the response is received\n252: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `True` (session already deleted)\n253: \n254: #### Scenario: Delete session other failure\n255: - **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session-err\")` is called and server returns 500\n256: - **WHEN** the error occurs\n257: - **THEN** the method SHALL log the error and return `False`\n258: \n259: ### Requirement: Verbose mode logging\n260: The system SHALL support verbose mode for debug logging across client operations.\n261: \n262: #### Scenario: Verbose mode enabled\n263: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(verbose=True)` is initialized\n264: - **WHEN** operations like command execution or file transfers occur\n265: - **THEN** the client SHALL log debug-level messages including request details, response status, and timing information\n266: \n267: #### Scenario: Verbose mode disabled\n268: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(verbose=False)` is initialized (default)\n269: - **WHEN** operations occur\n270: - **THEN** the client SHALL log only INFO-level and above messages (errors, warnings, info)\n271: \n272: ### Requirement: TTL parameter handling\n273: The system SHALL use the TTL parameter when creating sessions for session expiration control.\n274: \n275: #### Scenario: Custom TTL for session creation\n276: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(ttl=7200)` is initialized without `session_id`\n277: - **WHEN** a new session is created via control plane\n278: - **THEN** the request body SHALL include `ttl: 7200` to set session expiration to 2 hours\n279: \n280: #### Scenario: Default TTL when not specified\n281: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient()` is initialized without explicit TTL\n282: - **WHEN** a new session is created\n283: - **THEN** the request body SHALL include `ttl: 3600` (default 1 hour)\n284: \n285: ### Requirement: Namespace parameter propagation\n286: The system SHALL propagate namespace parameter through control plane and data plane URL construction.\n287: \n288: #### Scenario: Custom namespace in constructor\n289: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(namespace=\"production\")` is initialized\n290: - **WHEN** session is created and data plane is initialized\n291: - **THEN** the control plane request SHALL include `namespace: \"production\"` and data plane base URL SHALL include `/namespaces/production/`\n292: \n293: #### Scenario: Default namespace\n294: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient()` is initialized without namespace\n295: - **WHEN** initialization completes\n296: - **THEN** namespace SHALL default to `\"default\"` in both control plane request and data plane URL\n297: \n298: ### Requirement: Metadata support in session creation\n299: The system SHALL support optional metadata dictionary when creating sessions.\n300: \n301: #### Scenario: Session with metadata\n302: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient.create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"dev\", metadata={\"owner\": \"user1\", \"purpose\": \"data-analysis\"})` is called\n303: - **WHEN** the request body is prepared\n304: - **THEN** the JSON SHALL include `metadata: {\"owner\": \"user1\", \"purpose\": \"data-analysis\"}`\n305: \n306: #### Scenario: Session without metadata\n307: - **GIVEN** `create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"dev\")` is called without metadata parameter\n308: - **WHEN** the request body is prepared\n309: - **THEN** the JSON SHALL include `metadata: null` or omit the metadata field\n310: \n311: ## Acceptance Criteria Summary\n312: \n313: 1. ✅ Client initialization resolves environment variables correctly\n314: 2. ✅ Context manager protocol properly manages lifecycle\n315: 3. ✅ Data plane failures trigger cleanup before re-raising\n316: 4. ✅ Commands execute with proper timeout and error handling\n317: 5. ✅ Code execution handles Python specially via file operations\n318: 6. ✅ File operations (write, upload, download, list) work correctly\n319: 7. ✅ HTTP sessions use connection pooling\n320: 8. ✅ Logging configured with appropriate levels\n321: 9. ✅ Session headers injected in all data plane requests\n322: 10. ✅ Base URLs constructed correctly for data plane\n323: 11. ✅ Control plane session create/delete work with 404 tolerance\n324: 12. ✅ Verbose mode provides debug logging when enabled\n325: 13. ✅ TTL and namespace parameters propagate correctly\n326: 14. ✅ Optional metadata supported in session creation\n327: \n328: ## Dependencies\n329: \n330: - `requests` library for HTTP client functionality\n331: - `PyJWT>=2.0.0` for JWT token handling (if needed)\n332: - `cryptography` for cryptographic operations (if needed)\n333: - Python >=3.10\n334: \n335: ## References\n336: \n337: - Base Design: `python-sdk/design.md`\n338: - Base Specification: `python-sdk/spec.md`\n339: - AR: AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n\n(End of file - total 339 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification: AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n\n## AR Metadata\n- **AR ID**: AR-027\n- **Title**: SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n- **Module**: sdk-python\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Status**: Implementation Required\n\n## Purpose\nThis delta specification defines implementation requirements for the `CodeInterpreterClient` class in the AgentCube Python SDK, focusing on session lifecycle management, code execution, file operations, and HTTP client interactions.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreterClient initialization with environment variable resolution\nThe system SHALL resolve `workload_manager_url` from parameter or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` environment variable, resolve `router_url` from parameter or `ROUTER_URL` environment variable (required), and resolve `auth_token` from parameter or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`.\n\n#### Scenario: All parameters provided explicitly\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(name=\"test\", namespace=\"dev\", ttl=1800, workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\", router_url=\"http://router:9000\", auth_token=\"custom-token\")` is called","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775879316213,"end":1775879316228}}}}
