{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879329921,"sessionID":"ses_28558a73bffe63pzmnHs6VtxMQ","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa81853001bf1Fy7uDGfzC0d","messageID":"msg_d7aa7e333001QMD6DH0Fl7Wjjg","sessionID":"ses_28558a73bffe63pzmnHs6VtxMQ","type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"toolu_tool-19c4f8ef94b1486ba9454f6c4c6e87d7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md","newString":"# Delta Specification: AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n\n## AR Metadata\n- **AR ID**: AR-029\n- **Title**: SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n- **Module**: sdk-python\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Status**: Implementation Required\n\n## Purpose\nThis delta specification defines implementation requirements for the HTTP底层客户端 components in the AgentCube Python SDK, including `ControlPlaneClient`, `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, and `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`. It focuses on HTTP session management, connection pooling, timeout configuration, header management, and exception handling across all HTTP client implementations.","oldString":"# Delta Specification: AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n\n## AR Metadata\n- **AR ID**: AR-027\n- **Title**: SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n- **Module**: sdk-python\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Status**: Implementation Required\n\n## Purpose\nThis delta specification defines implementation requirements for the `CodeInterpreterClient` class in the AgentCube Python SDK, focusing on session lifecycle management, code execution, file operations, and HTTP client interactions."},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"diff":"Index: /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md\n===================================================================\n--- /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md\n+++ /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md\n@@ -1,16 +1,16 @@\n-# Delta Specification: AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n+# Delta Specification: AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n \n ## AR Metadata\n-- **AR ID**: AR-027\n-- **Title**: SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n+- **AR ID**: AR-029\n+- **Title**: SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n - **Module**: sdk-python\n - **Language**: Python\n - **Size**: M\n - **Status**: Implementation Required\n \n ## Purpose\n-This delta specification defines implementation requirements for the `CodeInterpreterClient` class in the AgentCube Python SDK, focusing on session lifecycle management, code execution, file operations, and HTTP client interactions.\n+This delta specification defines implementation requirements for the HTTP底层客户端 components in the AgentCube Python SDK, including `ControlPlaneClient`, `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, and `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`. It focuses on HTTP session management, connection pooling, timeout configuration, header management, and exception handling across all HTTP client implementations.\n \n ## Requirements\n \n ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterClient initialization with environment variable resolution\n","filediff":{"file":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md","before":"# Delta Specification: AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n\n## AR Metadata\n- **AR ID**: AR-027\n- **Title**: SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n- **Module**: sdk-python\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Status**: Implementation Required\n\n## Purpose\nThis delta specification defines implementation requirements for the `CodeInterpreterClient` class in the AgentCube Python SDK, focusing on session lifecycle management, code execution, file operations, and HTTP client interactions.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreterClient initialization with environment variable resolution\nThe system SHALL resolve `workload_manager_url` from parameter or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` environment variable, resolve `router_url` from parameter or `ROUTER_URL` environment variable (required), and resolve `auth_token` from parameter or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`.\n\n#### Scenario: All parameters provided explicitly\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(name=\"test\", namespace=\"dev\", ttl=1800, workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\", router_url=\"http://router:9000\", auth_token=\"custom-token\")` is called\n- **WHEN** initialization completes\n- **THEN** the client SHALL use the provided `workload_manager_url`, `router_url`, and `auth_token` values directly\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager URL from environment\n- **GIVEN** environment variable `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` is set to `http://wm-default:8080`\n- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(router_url=\"http://router:9000\")` is called without `workload_manager_url`\n- **THEN** the client SHALL resolve `workload_manager_url` to `http://wm-default:8080`\n\n#### Scenario: Router URL missing required parameter\n- **GIVEN** neither `router_url` parameter nor `ROUTER_URL` environment variable is set\n- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient()` is initialized\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message containing \"Router URL must be provided\"\n\n#### Scenario: Auth token from Kubernetes service account\n- **GIVEN** `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` contains valid JWT token\n- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient()` is called without `auth_token` parameter\n- **THEN** the client SHALL read and use the token from the file path via `read_token_from_file`\n\n#### Scenario: Service account token file missing\n- **GIVEN** `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` does not exist\n- **WHEN** `auth_token` is not provided and `read_token_from_file` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return empty string and `auth_token` SHALL be set to `None` (no Authorization header will be set)\n\n### Requirement: Session lifecycle with context manager support\nThe system SHALL support context manager protocol via `__enter__` and `__exit__`, create session via control plane if `session_id` not provided, and cleanup resources on exit.\n\n#### Scenario: Context manager entry with existing session_id\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(session_id=\"existing-session\")` is created\n- **WHEN** the client enters a context manager block via `with client:`\n- **THEN** `__enter__` SHALL return `self` without creating a new session\n\n#### Scenario: Context manager entry creates new session\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient()` is created without `session_id`\n- **WHEN** the client enters a context manager block\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `ControlPlaneClient.create_session()`, set `session_id` to returned value, initialize `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, and return `self`\n\n#### Scenario: Context manager normal exit\n- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterClient` is used in a `with` block and `session_id` was created during entry\n- **WHEN** the block exits normally\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()`, which closes data-plane client, deletes control-plane session via `ControlPlaneClient.delete_session()`, and closes control-plane HTTP session\n\n#### Scenario: Context manager exit with exception\n- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterClient` is used in a `with` block and an exception occurs in the block\n- **WHEN** the block exits with exception\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()` to clean up resources, then re-raise the exception with exception info passed to `__exit__`\n\n#### Scenario: Manual stop after context manager\n- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterClient` has already exited its context manager and `stop()` was called\n- **WHEN** `stop()` is called again manually\n- **THEN** subsequent calls SHALL be idempotent and not raise errors\n\n### Requirement: Data plane initialization failure handling\nThe system SHALL handle data plane initialization failures by cleaning up created sessions before re-raising.\n\n#### Scenario: Data plane init fails after session creation\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` was not provided and `ControlPlaneClient.create_session()` succeeded returning \"new-session-123\"\n- **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises an exception during initialization\n- **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning message, call `ControlPlaneClient.delete_session(\"new-session-123\")`, set `session_id` to `None`, and re-raise the original exception\n\n#### Scenario: Data plane init fails with existing session\n- **GIVEN** `session_id=\"existing-456\"` was provided to constructor\n- **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises an exception\n- **THEN** the client SHALL NOT attempt to delete the session (as it was not created by this client), but SHALL re-raise the exception\n\n### Requirement: Command execution with timeout and error handling\nThe system SHALL execute shell commands via data plane, parse JSON response, handle non-zero exit codes, and support custom timeouts.\n\n#### Scenario: Successful command execution\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is initialized and session is active\n- **WHEN** `execute_command(\"echo 'hello world'\")` is called with default timeout\n- **THEN** the system SHALL POST to `api/execute` with JSON `{\"command\": [\"echo\", \"hello world\"], \"timeout\": \"120s\"}`, wait for response, and return `stdout` from response JSON\n\n#### Scenario: Command with non-zero exit code\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"ls /nonexistent\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the response JSON contains `exit_code: 1` and `stderr: \"No such file or directory\"`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError(exit_code=1, stderr=\"No such file or directory\", command=\"ls /nonexistent\")`\n\n#### Scenario: Custom timeout for command execution\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"sleep 10\", timeout=30.0)` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is prepared\n- **THEN** the body SHALL include `timeout: \"30s\"` and the HTTP read timeout SHALL be `32.0` seconds (30 + 2.0 buffer)\n\n#### Scenario: Command timeout without custom override\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"long-running-command\")` is called without timeout parameter\n- **WHEN** the default timeout is applied\n- **THEN** the body SHALL include `timeout: \"120s\"` (from `self.timeout`) and read timeout SHALL be `122.0` seconds\n\n#### Scenario: Command with list argument format\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command([\"ls\", \"-la\", \"/tmp\"])` is called with list of strings\n- **WHEN** the command is executed\n- **THEN** the data plane SHALL receive the list directly in the JSON body `{\"command\": [\"ls\", \"-la\", \"/tmp\"], \"timeout\": \"120s\"}`\n\n### Requirement: Code execution with language-specific handling\nThe system SHALL support `run_code()` for multiple languages with special handling for Python via file write and execute.\n\n#### Scenario: Python code execution\n- **GIVEN** `run_code(language=\"python\", code=\"print('hello')\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the method executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL generate timestamped filename (e.g., `code_20250411_123456.py`), call `write_file(content=\"print('hello')\", remote_path=\"<filename>\")`, then call `execute_command(f\"python3 {filename}\")` and return result\n\n#### Scenario: Python code with alternative language identifier\n- **GIVEN** `run_code(language=\"py\", code=\"x = 1 + 2; print(x)\")` is called\n- **WHEN** language is detected as Python variant\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use the same file-write-and-execute pattern as `\"python\"` or `\"python3\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Non-Python code execution\n- **GIVEN** `run_code(language=\"bash\", code=\"echo 'hello from bash'\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the language is not a Python variant\n- **THEN** the system SHALL POST directly to data plane `run_code` endpoint with `{\"language\": \"bash\", \"code\": \"echo 'hello from bash'\"}` body\n\n### Requirement: File operations via data plane\nThe system SHALL support write, upload, download, and list file operations with proper encoding and headers.\n\n#### Scenario: Write file with base64 encoding\n- **GIVEN** `write_file(content=\"hello world\", remote_path=\"/tmp/test.txt\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** the system SHALL POST to `api/files` with JSON `{\"content\": \"<base64>\", \"path\": \"/tmp/test.txt\", \"mode\": \"0644\"}` where content is base64-encoded\n\n#### Scenario: Upload file via multipart\n- **GIVEN** `upload_file(local_path=\"/local/file.txt\", remote_path=\"/remote/file.txt\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the multipart request is sent\n- **THEN** the system SHALL POST to `api/files` with `files={'file': open('/local/file.txt', 'rb')}`, `data={'path': '/remote/file.txt', 'mode': '0644'}`, and header `x-agentcube-session-id: <session_id>`\n\n#### Scenario: Download file with streaming\n- **GIVEN** `download_file(remote_path=\"/data/result.json\", local_path=\"./result.json\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the file is downloaded\n- **THEN** the system SHALL GET `api/files/data/result.json` (cleaned path) with `stream=True`, write response content to `./result.json`, and close response after writing\n\n#### Scenario: List files in directory\n- **GIVEN** `list_files(path=\"/home/user\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the request completes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL GET `api/files?path=/home/user` and return the JSON response (typically file listing)\n\n#### Scenario: List files default path\n- **GIVEN** `list_files()` is called without path argument\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use default path `.` and query `api/files?path=.`\n\n### Requirement: HTTP session management and connection pooling\nThe system SHALL use `requests.Session` with `HTTPAdapter` for connection pooling on control plane and data plane clients.\n\n#### Scenario: Create session with default pool settings\n- **GIVEN** `create_session()` is called without arguments\n- **WHEN** the session is created\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create `requests.Session`, mount `HTTPAdapter` with `pool_connections=10` and `pool_maxsize=10` for both `http://` and `https://`, and return the session\n\n#### Scenario: Control plane client with custom pool settings\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(pool_connections=20, pool_maxsize=20)` is initialized\n- **WHEN** the HTTP session is created\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use the custom pool values when calling `create_session()`\n\n#### Scenario: Data plane client uses provided session\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is constructed with all required parameters\n- **WHEN** initialization completes\n- **THEN** the client SHALL create its own HTTP session via `create_session()` with configured pool settings\n\n#### Scenario: Closing sessions\n- **GIVEN** a client has an active `requests.Session`\n- **WHEN** `close()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `self.session.close()` to properly close the session and release connections\n\n### Requirement: Logger configuration\nThe system SHALL configure logging with `get_logger()` utility supporting name and level parameters.\n\n#### Scenario: Logger with default INFO level\n- **GIVEN** `get_logger(\"agentcube.code_interpreter\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the logger is created\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return a `logging.Logger` instance with name `\"agentcube.code_interpreter\"` and level `logging.INFO`\n\n#### Scenario: Logger with custom level\n- **GIVEN** `get_logger(\"agentcube.client\", level=logging.DEBUG)` is called\n- **WHEN** the logger is created\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return a logger with level set to `logging.DEBUG`\n\n#### Scenario: Client initialization sets logger\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(verbose=True)` is initialized\n- **WHEN** the logger is set\n- **THEN** the client SHALL create logger with level based on `verbose` flag (DEBUG if True, INFO if False)\n\n### Requirement: Session header injection for data plane requests\nThe system SHALL inject `x-agentcube-session-id` header into all data plane requests.\n\n#### Scenario: Request includes session header\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(session_id=\"session-abc\")` is initialized\n- **WHEN** any `_request()` method call is made\n- **THEN** the request headers SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: session-abc`\n\n#### Scenario: Multipart upload includes session header\n- **GIVEN** `upload_file()` is called\n- **WHEN** the multipart POST is prepared\n- **THEN** the request SHALL explicitly set `x-agentcube-session-id` header alongside the multipart files and data\n\n#### Scenario: JSON request includes session header\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command()` is called with a JSON body\n- **WHEN** the POST request is sent\n- **THEN** the request SHALL include both `Content-Type: application/json` and `x-agentcube-session-id: <session_id>` headers\n\n### Requirement: Base URL construction for data plane\nThe system SHALL construct data plane base URL from router URL, namespace, and CR name unless explicitly provided.\n\n#### Scenario: Base URL from router and metadata\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(router_url=\"http://router:9000\", namespace=\"default\", cr_name=\"my-interpreter\")` is initialized without `base_url`\n- **WHEN** the base URL is constructed\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `http://router:9000/v1/namespaces/default/code-interpreters/my-interpreter/invocations/`\n\n#### Scenario: Explicit base URL overrides construction\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(base_url=\"http://custom:8080/custom/path/\")` is provided\n- **WHEN** initialization completes\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `http://custom:8080/custom/path/` without any router-based construction\n\n### Requirement: Control plane session creation and deletion\nThe system SHALL create sessions via POST to control plane API and delete via DELETE with 404 tolerance.\n\n#### Scenario: Create session returns session ID\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(base_url=\"http://wm:8080\")` is initialized\n- **WHEN** `create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"dev\", ttl=1800, metadata={\"key\": \"value\"})` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL POST `http://wm:8080/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON body containing all parameters and return the `sessionId` from response\n\n#### Scenario: Create session missing session ID in response\n- **GIVEN** the control plane POST succeeds but response JSON lacks `sessionId` field\n- **WHEN** the response is parsed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating missing `sessionId`\n\n#### Scenario: Delete session success\n- **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session-123\")` is called and server returns 200 or 204\n- **WHEN** the response is processed\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`\n\n#### Scenario: Delete session 404 treated as success\n- **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session-404\")` is called and server returns 404\n- **WHEN** the response is received\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return `True` (session already deleted)\n\n#### Scenario: Delete session other failure\n- **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session-err\")` is called and server returns 500\n- **WHEN** the error occurs\n- **THEN** the method SHALL log the error and return `False`\n\n### Requirement: Verbose mode logging\nThe system SHALL support verbose mode for debug logging across client operations.\n\n#### Scenario: Verbose mode enabled\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(verbose=True)` is initialized\n- **WHEN** operations like command execution or file transfers occur\n- **THEN** the client SHALL log debug-level messages including request details, response status, and timing information\n\n#### Scenario: Verbose mode disabled\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(verbose=False)` is initialized (default)\n- **WHEN** operations occur\n- **THEN** the client SHALL log only INFO-level and above messages (errors, warnings, info)\n\n### Requirement: TTL parameter handling\nThe system SHALL use the TTL parameter when creating sessions for session expiration control.\n\n#### Scenario: Custom TTL for session creation\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(ttl=7200)` is initialized without `session_id`\n- **WHEN** a new session is created via control plane\n- **THEN** the request body SHALL include `ttl: 7200` to set session expiration to 2 hours\n\n#### Scenario: Default TTL when not specified\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient()` is initialized without explicit TTL\n- **WHEN** a new session is created\n- **THEN** the request body SHALL include `ttl: 3600` (default 1 hour)\n\n### Requirement: Namespace parameter propagation\nThe system SHALL propagate namespace parameter through control plane and data plane URL construction.\n\n#### Scenario: Custom namespace in constructor\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(namespace=\"production\")` is initialized\n- **WHEN** session is created and data plane is initialized\n- **THEN** the control plane request SHALL include `namespace: \"production\"` and data plane base URL SHALL include `/namespaces/production/`\n\n#### Scenario: Default namespace\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient()` is initialized without namespace\n- **WHEN** initialization completes\n- **THEN** namespace SHALL default to `\"default\"` in both control plane request and data plane URL\n\n### Requirement: Metadata support in session creation\nThe system SHALL support optional metadata dictionary when creating sessions.\n\n#### Scenario: Session with metadata\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient.create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"dev\", metadata={\"owner\": \"user1\", \"purpose\": \"data-analysis\"})` is called\n- **WHEN** the request body is prepared\n- **THEN** the JSON SHALL include `metadata: {\"owner\": \"user1\", \"purpose\": \"data-analysis\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Session without metadata\n- **GIVEN** `create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"dev\")` is called without metadata parameter\n- **WHEN** the request body is prepared\n- **THEN** the JSON SHALL include `metadata: null` or omit the metadata field\n\n## Acceptance Criteria Summary\n\n1. ✅ Client initialization resolves environment variables correctly\n2. ✅ Context manager protocol properly manages lifecycle\n3. ✅ Data plane failures trigger cleanup before re-raising\n4. ✅ Commands execute with proper timeout and error handling\n5. ✅ Code execution handles Python specially via file operations\n6. ✅ File operations (write, upload, download, list) work correctly\n7. ✅ HTTP sessions use connection pooling\n8. ✅ Logging configured with appropriate levels\n9. ✅ Session headers injected in all data plane requests\n10. ✅ Base URLs constructed correctly for data plane\n11. ✅ Control plane session create/delete work with 404 tolerance\n12. ✅ Verbose mode provides debug logging when enabled\n13. ✅ TTL and namespace parameters propagate correctly\n14. ✅ Optional metadata supported in session creation\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- `requests` library for HTTP client functionality\n- `PyJWT>=2.0.0` for JWT token handling (if needed)\n- `cryptography` for cryptographic operations (if needed)\n- Python >=3.10\n\n## References\n\n- Base Design: `python-sdk/design.md`\n- Base Specification: `python-sdk/spec.md`\n- AR: AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient","after":"# Delta Specification: AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n\n## AR Metadata\n- **AR ID**: AR-029\n- **Title**: SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n- **Module**: sdk-python\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Status**: Implementation Required\n\n## Purpose\nThis delta specification defines implementation requirements for the HTTP底层客户端 components in the AgentCube Python SDK, including `ControlPlaneClient`, `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, and `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`. It focuses on HTTP session management, connection pooling, timeout configuration, header management, and exception handling across all HTTP client implementations.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreterClient initialization with environment variable resolution\nThe system SHALL resolve `workload_manager_url` from parameter or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` environment variable, resolve `router_url` from parameter or `ROUTER_URL` environment variable (required), and resolve `auth_token` from parameter or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`.\n\n#### Scenario: All parameters provided explicitly\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(name=\"test\", namespace=\"dev\", ttl=1800, workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\", router_url=\"http://router:9000\", auth_token=\"custom-token\")` is called\n- **WHEN** initialization completes\n- **THEN** the client SHALL use the provided `workload_manager_url`, `router_url`, and `auth_token` values directly\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager URL from environment\n- **GIVEN** environment variable `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` is set to `http://wm-default:8080`\n- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(router_url=\"http://router:9000\")` is called without `workload_manager_url`\n- **THEN** the client SHALL resolve `workload_manager_url` to `http://wm-default:8080`\n\n#### Scenario: Router URL missing required parameter\n- **GIVEN** neither `router_url` parameter nor `ROUTER_URL` environment variable is set\n- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient()` is initialized\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message containing \"Router URL must be provided\"\n\n#### Scenario: Auth token from Kubernetes service account\n- **GIVEN** `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` contains valid JWT token\n- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient()` is called without `auth_token` parameter\n- **THEN** the client SHALL read and use the token from the file path via `read_token_from_file`\n\n#### Scenario: Service account token file missing\n- **GIVEN** `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` does not exist\n- **WHEN** `auth_token` is not provided and `read_token_from_file` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return empty string and `auth_token` SHALL be set to `None` (no Authorization header will be set)\n\n### Requirement: Session lifecycle with context manager support\nThe system SHALL support context manager protocol via `__enter__` and `__exit__`, create session via control plane if `session_id` not provided, and cleanup resources on exit.\n\n#### Scenario: Context manager entry with existing session_id\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(session_id=\"existing-session\")` is created\n- **WHEN** the client enters a context manager block via `with client:`\n- **THEN** `__enter__` SHALL return `self` without creating a new session\n\n#### Scenario: Context manager entry creates new session\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient()` is created without `session_id`\n- **WHEN** the client enters a context manager block\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `ControlPlaneClient.create_session()`, set `session_id` to returned value, initialize `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, and return `self`\n\n#### Scenario: Context manager normal exit\n- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterClient` is used in a `with` block and `session_id` was created during entry\n- **WHEN** the block exits normally\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()`, which closes data-plane client, deletes control-plane session via `ControlPlaneClient.delete_session()`, and closes control-plane HTTP session\n\n#### Scenario: Context manager exit with exception\n- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterClient` is used in a `with` block and an exception occurs in the block\n- **WHEN** the block exits with exception\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()` to clean up resources, then re-raise the exception with exception info passed to `__exit__`\n\n#### Scenario: Manual stop after context manager\n- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterClient` has already exited its context manager and `stop()` was called\n- **WHEN** `stop()` is called again manually\n- **THEN** subsequent calls SHALL be idempotent and not raise errors\n\n### Requirement: Data plane initialization failure handling\nThe system SHALL handle data plane initialization failures by cleaning up created sessions before re-raising.\n\n#### Scenario: Data plane init fails after session creation\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` was not provided and `ControlPlaneClient.create_session()` succeeded returning \"new-session-123\"\n- **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises an exception during initialization\n- **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning message, call `ControlPlaneClient.delete_session(\"new-session-123\")`, set `session_id` to `None`, and re-raise the original exception\n\n#### Scenario: Data plane init fails with existing session\n- **GIVEN** `session_id=\"existing-456\"` was provided to constructor\n- **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises an exception\n- **THEN** the client SHALL NOT attempt to delete the session (as it was not created by this client), but SHALL re-raise the exception\n\n### Requirement: Command execution with timeout and error handling\nThe system SHALL execute shell commands via data plane, parse JSON response, handle non-zero exit codes, and support custom timeouts.\n\n#### Scenario: Successful command execution\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is initialized and session is active\n- **WHEN** `execute_command(\"echo 'hello world'\")` is called with default timeout\n- **THEN** the system SHALL POST to `api/execute` with JSON `{\"command\": [\"echo\", \"hello world\"], \"timeout\": \"120s\"}`, wait for response, and return `stdout` from response JSON\n\n#### Scenario: Command with non-zero exit code\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"ls /nonexistent\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the response JSON contains `exit_code: 1` and `stderr: \"No such file or directory\"`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError(exit_code=1, stderr=\"No such file or directory\", command=\"ls /nonexistent\")`\n\n#### Scenario: Custom timeout for command execution\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"sleep 10\", timeout=30.0)` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is prepared\n- **THEN** the body SHALL include `timeout: \"30s\"` and the HTTP read timeout SHALL be `32.0` seconds (30 + 2.0 buffer)\n\n#### Scenario: Command timeout without custom override\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"long-running-command\")` is called without timeout parameter\n- **WHEN** the default timeout is applied\n- **THEN** the body SHALL include `timeout: \"120s\"` (from `self.timeout`) and read timeout SHALL be `122.0` seconds\n\n#### Scenario: Command with list argument format\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command([\"ls\", \"-la\", \"/tmp\"])` is called with list of strings\n- **WHEN** the command is executed\n- **THEN** the data plane SHALL receive the list directly in the JSON body `{\"command\": [\"ls\", \"-la\", \"/tmp\"], \"timeout\": \"120s\"}`\n\n### Requirement: Code execution with language-specific handling\nThe system SHALL support `run_code()` for multiple languages with special handling for Python via file write and execute.\n\n#### Scenario: Python code execution\n- **GIVEN** `run_code(language=\"python\", code=\"print('hello')\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the method executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL generate timestamped filename (e.g., `code_20250411_123456.py`), call `write_file(content=\"print('hello')\", remote_path=\"<filename>\")`, then call `execute_command(f\"python3 {filename}\")` and return result\n\n#### Scenario: Python code with alternative language identifier\n- **GIVEN** `run_code(language=\"py\", code=\"x = 1 + 2; print(x)\")` is called\n- **WHEN** language is detected as Python variant\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use the same file-write-and-execute pattern as `\"python\"` or `\"python3\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Non-Python code execution\n- **GIVEN** `run_code(language=\"bash\", code=\"echo 'hello from bash'\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the language is not a Python variant\n- **THEN** the system SHALL POST directly to data plane `run_code` endpoint with `{\"language\": \"bash\", \"code\": \"echo 'hello from bash'\"}` body\n\n### Requirement: File operations via data plane\nThe system SHALL support write, upload, download, and list file operations with proper encoding and headers.\n\n#### Scenario: Write file with base64 encoding\n- **GIVEN** `write_file(content=\"hello world\", remote_path=\"/tmp/test.txt\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** the system SHALL POST to `api/files` with JSON `{\"content\": \"<base64>\", \"path\": \"/tmp/test.txt\", \"mode\": \"0644\"}` where content is base64-encoded\n\n#### Scenario: Upload file via multipart\n- **GIVEN** `upload_file(local_path=\"/local/file.txt\", remote_path=\"/remote/file.txt\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the multipart request is sent\n- **THEN** the system SHALL POST to `api/files` with `files={'file': open('/local/file.txt', 'rb')}`, `data={'path': '/remote/file.txt', 'mode': '0644'}`, and header `x-agentcube-session-id: <session_id>`\n\n#### Scenario: Download file with streaming\n- **GIVEN** `download_file(remote_path=\"/data/result.json\", local_path=\"./result.json\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the file is downloaded\n- **THEN** the system SHALL GET `api/files/data/result.json` (cleaned path) with `stream=True`, write response content to `./result.json`, and close response after writing\n\n#### Scenario: List files in directory\n- **GIVEN** `list_files(path=\"/home/user\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the request completes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL GET `api/files?path=/home/user` and return the JSON response (typically file listing)\n\n#### Scenario: List files default path\n- **GIVEN** `list_files()` is called without path argument\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use default path `.` and query `api/files?path=.`\n\n### Requirement: HTTP session management and connection pooling\nThe system SHALL use `requests.Session` with `HTTPAdapter` for connection pooling on control plane and data plane clients.\n\n#### Scenario: Create session with default pool settings\n- **GIVEN** `create_session()` is called without arguments\n- **WHEN** the session is created\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create `requests.Session`, mount `HTTPAdapter` with `pool_connections=10` and `pool_maxsize=10` for both `http://` and `https://`, and return the session\n\n#### Scenario: Control plane client with custom pool settings\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(pool_connections=20, pool_maxsize=20)` is initialized\n- **WHEN** the HTTP session is created\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use the custom pool values when calling `create_session()`\n\n#### Scenario: Data plane client uses provided session\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is constructed with all required parameters\n- **WHEN** initialization completes\n- **THEN** the client SHALL create its own HTTP session via `create_session()` with configured pool settings\n\n#### Scenario: Closing sessions\n- **GIVEN** a client has an active `requests.Session`\n- **WHEN** `close()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `self.session.close()` to properly close the session and release connections\n\n### Requirement: Logger configuration\nThe system SHALL configure logging with `get_logger()` utility supporting name and level parameters.\n\n#### Scenario: Logger with default INFO level\n- **GIVEN** `get_logger(\"agentcube.code_interpreter\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the logger is created\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return a `logging.Logger` instance with name `\"agentcube.code_interpreter\"` and level `logging.INFO`\n\n#### Scenario: Logger with custom level\n- **GIVEN** `get_logger(\"agentcube.client\", level=logging.DEBUG)` is called\n- **WHEN** the logger is created\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return a logger with level set to `logging.DEBUG`\n\n#### Scenario: Client initialization sets logger\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(verbose=True)` is initialized\n- **WHEN** the logger is set\n- **THEN** the client SHALL create logger with level based on `verbose` flag (DEBUG if True, INFO if False)\n\n### Requirement: Session header injection for data plane requests\nThe system SHALL inject `x-agentcube-session-id` header into all data plane requests.\n\n#### Scenario: Request includes session header\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(session_id=\"session-abc\")` is initialized\n- **WHEN** any `_request()` method call is made\n- **THEN** the request headers SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: session-abc`\n\n#### Scenario: Multipart upload includes session header\n- **GIVEN** `upload_file()` is called\n- **WHEN** the multipart POST is prepared\n- **THEN** the request SHALL explicitly set `x-agentcube-session-id` header alongside the multipart files and data\n\n#### Scenario: JSON request includes session header\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command()` is called with a JSON body\n- **WHEN** the POST request is sent\n- **THEN** the request SHALL include both `Content-Type: application/json` and `x-agentcube-session-id: <session_id>` headers\n\n### Requirement: Base URL construction for data plane\nThe system SHALL construct data plane base URL from router URL, namespace, and CR name unless explicitly provided.\n\n#### Scenario: Base URL from router and metadata\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(router_url=\"http://router:9000\", namespace=\"default\", cr_name=\"my-interpreter\")` is initialized without `base_url`\n- **WHEN** the base URL is constructed\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `http://router:9000/v1/namespaces/default/code-interpreters/my-interpreter/invocations/`\n\n#### Scenario: Explicit base URL overrides construction\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(base_url=\"http://custom:8080/custom/path/\")` is provided\n- **WHEN** initialization completes\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `http://custom:8080/custom/path/` without any router-based construction\n\n### Requirement: Control plane session creation and deletion\nThe system SHALL create sessions via POST to control plane API and delete via DELETE with 404 tolerance.\n\n#### Scenario: Create session returns session ID\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(base_url=\"http://wm:8080\")` is initialized\n- **WHEN** `create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"dev\", ttl=1800, metadata={\"key\": \"value\"})` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL POST `http://wm:8080/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON body containing all parameters and return the `sessionId` from response\n\n#### Scenario: Create session missing session ID in response\n- **GIVEN** the control plane POST succeeds but response JSON lacks `sessionId` field\n- **WHEN** the response is parsed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating missing `sessionId`\n\n#### Scenario: Delete session success\n- **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session-123\")` is called and server returns 200 or 204\n- **WHEN** the response is processed\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`\n\n#### Scenario: Delete session 404 treated as success\n- **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session-404\")` is called and server returns 404\n- **WHEN** the response is received\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return `True` (session already deleted)\n\n#### Scenario: Delete session other failure\n- **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session-err\")` is called and server returns 500\n- **WHEN** the error occurs\n- **THEN** the method SHALL log the error and return `False`\n\n### Requirement: Verbose mode logging\nThe system SHALL support verbose mode for debug logging across client operations.\n\n#### Scenario: Verbose mode enabled\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(verbose=True)` is initialized\n- **WHEN** operations like command execution or file transfers occur\n- **THEN** the client SHALL log debug-level messages including request details, response status, and timing information\n\n#### Scenario: Verbose mode disabled\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(verbose=False)` is initialized (default)\n- **WHEN** operations occur\n- **THEN** the client SHALL log only INFO-level and above messages (errors, warnings, info)\n\n### Requirement: TTL parameter handling\nThe system SHALL use the TTL parameter when creating sessions for session expiration control.\n\n#### Scenario: Custom TTL for session creation\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(ttl=7200)` is initialized without `session_id`\n- **WHEN** a new session is created via control plane\n- **THEN** the request body SHALL include `ttl: 7200` to set session expiration to 2 hours\n\n#### Scenario: Default TTL when not specified\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient()` is initialized without explicit TTL\n- **WHEN** a new session is created\n- **THEN** the request body SHALL include `ttl: 3600` (default 1 hour)\n\n### Requirement: Namespace parameter propagation\nThe system SHALL propagate namespace parameter through control plane and data plane URL construction.\n\n#### Scenario: Custom namespace in constructor\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(namespace=\"production\")` is initialized\n- **WHEN** session is created and data plane is initialized\n- **THEN** the control plane request SHALL include `namespace: \"production\"` and data plane base URL SHALL include `/namespaces/production/`\n\n#### Scenario: Default namespace\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient()` is initialized without namespace\n- **WHEN** initialization completes\n- **THEN** namespace SHALL default to `\"default\"` in both control plane request and data plane URL\n\n### Requirement: Metadata support in session creation\nThe system SHALL support optional metadata dictionary when creating sessions.\n\n#### Scenario: Session with metadata\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient.create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"dev\", metadata={\"owner\": \"user1\", \"purpose\": \"data-analysis\"})` is called\n- **WHEN** the request body is prepared\n- **THEN** the JSON SHALL include `metadata: {\"owner\": \"user1\", \"purpose\": \"data-analysis\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Session without metadata\n- **GIVEN** `create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"dev\")` is called without metadata parameter\n- **WHEN** the request body is prepared\n- **THEN** the JSON SHALL include `metadata: null` or omit the metadata field\n\n## Acceptance Criteria Summary\n\n1. ✅ Client initialization resolves environment variables correctly\n2. ✅ Context manager protocol properly manages lifecycle\n3. ✅ Data plane failures trigger cleanup before re-raising\n4. ✅ Commands execute with proper timeout and error handling\n5. ✅ Code execution handles Python specially via file operations\n6. ✅ File operations (write, upload, download, list) work correctly\n7. ✅ HTTP sessions use connection pooling\n8. ✅ Logging configured with appropriate levels\n9. ✅ Session headers injected in all data plane requests\n10. ✅ Base URLs constructed correctly for data plane\n11. ✅ Control plane session create/delete work with 404 tolerance\n12. ✅ Verbose mode provides debug logging when enabled\n13. ✅ TTL and namespace parameters propagate correctly\n14. ✅ Optional metadata supported in session creation\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- `requests` library for HTTP client functionality\n- `PyJWT>=2.0.0` for JWT token handling (if needed)\n- `cryptography` for cryptographic operations (if needed)\n- Python >=3.10\n\n## References\n\n- Base Design: `python-sdk/design.md`\n- Base Specification: `python-sdk/spec.md`\n- AR: AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient","additions":4,"deletions":4},"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775879329903,"end":1775879329918}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775879329942,"sessionID":"ses_28558a73bffe63pzmnHs6VtxMQ","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa81880001Rf89v4B8yHjdCA","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7aa7e333001QMD6DH0Fl7Wjjg","sessionID":"ses_28558a73bffe63pzmnHs6VtxMQ","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":29613,"input":14129,"output":445,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":15039}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775879333106,"sessionID":"ses_28558a73bffe63pzmnHs6VtxMQ","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa824eb001Wmshs52P9ZC8Q8","messageID":"msg_d7aa818ad001WM5WCqDzPyRbWy","sessionID":"ses_28558a73bffe63pzmnHs6VtxMQ","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879444498,"sessionID":"ses_28558a73bffe63pzmnHs6VtxMQ","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa9d751001VebNZpS5K7gIL1","messageID":"msg_d7aa818ad001WM5WCqDzPyRbWy","sessionID":"ses_28558a73bffe63pzmnHs6VtxMQ","type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"toolu_tool-55d08fda10d34af2bdc8dc07ca657188","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md","newString":"## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient initialization with environment variable resolution\nThe system SHALL resolve `base_url` from `workload_manager_url` parameter or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` environment variable, and resolve `auth_token` from parameter or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`.\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager URL from parameter\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\")` is called\n- **WHEN** initialization completes\n- **THEN** the client SHALL use `http://wm:8080` as `base_url` directly\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager URL from environment\n- **GIVEN** environment variable `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` is set to `http://wm-default:8080`\n- **WHEN** `ControlPlaneClient()` is called without `workload_manager_url`\n- **THEN** the client SHALL resolve `base_url` to `http://wm-default:8080`\n\n#### Scenario: Auth token from Kubernetes service account\n- **GIVEN** `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` contains valid JWT token\n- **WHEN** `ControlPlaneClient()` is called without `auth_token` parameter\n- **THEN** the client SHALL read and use the token from the file path via `read_token_from_file`\n\n#### Scenario: Service account token file missing\n- **GIVEN** `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` does not exist\n- **WHEN** `auth_token` is not provided and `read_token_from_file` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return empty string and no `Authorization` header will be set on the session\n\n### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient session creation via HTTP POST\nThe system SHALL create sessions by POSTing to `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with proper headers and JSON body.\n\n#### Scenario: Create session with all parameters\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(base_url=\"http://wm:8080\")` is initialized\n- **WHEN** `create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"dev\", ttl=1800, metadata={\"key\": \"value\"})` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL POST `http://wm:8080/v1/code-interpreter` with `Content-Type: application/json`, `Authorization: Bearer {token}` (if token present), and JSON body `{\"name\": \"test\", \"namespace\": \"dev\", \"ttl\": 1800, \"metadata\": {\"key\": \"value\"}}`\n\n#### Scenario: Create session returns session ID\n- **GIVEN** the control plane POST succeeds with response `{\"sessionId\": \"new-session-123\", ...}`\n- **WHEN** the response is parsed\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return `\"new-session-123\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Create session missing session ID in response\n- **GIVEN** the control plane POST succeeds but response JSON lacks `sessionId` field\n- **WHEN** the response is parsed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating missing `sessionId`\n\n### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient session deletion via HTTP DELETE with 404 tolerance\nThe system SHALL delete sessions by DELETEing to `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` with 404 treated as success.\n\n#### Scenario: Delete session success\n- **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session-123\")` is called and server returns 200 or 204\n- **WHEN** the response is processed\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`\n\n#### Scenario: Delete session 404 treated as success\n- **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session-404\")` is called and server returns 404\n- **WHEN** the response is received\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return `True` (session already deleted)\n\n#### Scenario: Delete session other failure\n- **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session-err\")` is called and server returns 500\n- **WHEN** the error occurs\n- **THEN** the method SHALL log the error and return `False`\n\n### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient timeout and connection pooling configuration\nThe system SHALL use configurable timeouts and connection pooling via `HTTPAdapter`.\n\n#### Scenario: Default timeout and pool settings\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient()` is initialized without timeout parameters\n- **WHEN** requests are made\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, and `pool_maxsize=10`\n\n#### Scenario: Custom timeout and pool settings\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(timeout=300, connect_timeout=10.0, pool_connections=20, pool_maxsize=20)` is initialized\n- **WHEN** requests are made\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use the custom values for timeouts and connection pooling\n\n#### Scenario: Timeout tuple applied to requests\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)` is initialized\n- **WHEN** any HTTP request is made\n- **THEN** the request timeout SHALL be `(5.0, 120)` (connect, read)\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient base URL construction\nThe system SHALL construct base URL from router URL, namespace, and CR name unless explicitly provided.\n\n#### Scenario: Base URL from router and metadata\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(router_url=\"http://router:9000\", namespace=\"default\", cr_name=\"my-interpreter\")` is initialized without `base_url`\n- **WHEN** the base URL is constructed\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `http://router:9000/v1/namespaces/default/code-interpreters/my-interpreter/invocations/`\n\n#### Scenario: Explicit base URL overrides construction\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(base_url=\"http://custom:8080/custom/path/\")` is provided\n- **WHEN** initialization completes\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `http://custom:8080/custom/path/` without any router-based construction\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient session header injection\nThe system SHALL inject `x-agentcube-session-id` header into all requests using lowercase header name.\n\n#### Scenario: Request includes session header\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(session_id=\"session-abc\")` is initialized\n- **WHEN** any `_request()` method call is made\n- **THEN** the request headers SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: session-abc`\n\n#### Scenario: Multipart upload includes session header\n- **GIVEN** `upload_file()` is called\n- **WHEN** the multipart POST is prepared\n- **THEN** the request SHALL explicitly set `x-agentcube-session-id` header alongside the multipart files and data\n\n#### Scenario: JSON request includes session header\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command()` is called with a JSON body\n- **WHEN** the POST request is sent\n- **THEN** the request SHALL include both `Content-Type: application/json` and `x-agentcube-session-id: <session_id>` headers\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient execute command with timeout buffer\nThe system SHALL POST to `api/execute` with JSON body and apply read timeout buffer to avoid premature ReadTimeout.\n\n#### Scenario: Execute command with default timeout\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"echo hello\")` is called without timeout parameter\n- **WHEN** the request is prepared\n- **THEN** the body SHALL be `{\"command\": [\"echo\", \"hello\"], \"timeout\": \"120s\"}` and HTTP read timeout SHALL be `122.0` seconds (120 + 2.0 buffer)\n\n#### Scenario: Execute command with custom timeout\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"sleep 10\", timeout=30.0)` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is prepared\n- **THEN** the body SHALL include `timeout: \"30s\"` and the HTTP read timeout SHALL be `32.0` seconds (30 + 2.0 buffer)\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient file operations\nThe system SHALL support write, upload, download, and list file operations with proper encoding and headers.\n\n#### Scenario: Write file with base64 encoding\n- **GIVEN** `write_file(content=\"hello world\", remote_path=\"/tmp/test.txt\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** the system SHALL POST to `api/files` with JSON `{\"content\": \"<base64>\", \"path\": \"/tmp/test.txt\", \"mode\": \"0644\"}` where content is base64-encoded\n\n#### Scenario: Upload file via multipart\n- **GIVEN** `upload_file(local_path=\"/local/file.txt\", remote_path=\"/remote/file.txt\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the multipart request is sent\n- **THEN** the system SHALL POST to `api/files` with `files={'file': open('/local/file.txt', 'rb')}`, `data={'path': '/remote/file.txt', 'mode': '0644'}`, and header `x-agentcube-session-id: <session_id>`\n\n#### Scenario: Download file with streaming\n- **GIVEN** `download_file(remote_path=\"/data/result.json\", local_path=\"./result.json\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the file is downloaded\n- **THEN** the system SHALL GET `api/files/data/result.json` (cleaned path) with `stream=True`, write response content to `./result.json`, and close response after writing\n\n#### Scenario: List files in directory\n- **GIVEN** `list_files(path=\"/home/user\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the request completes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL GET `api/files?path=/home/user` and return the JSON response\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient base URL construction\nThe system SHALL construct base URL from router URL, namespace, and agent name.\n\n#### Scenario: Base URL from router and agent metadata\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(router_url=\"http://router:9000\", namespace=\"default\", agent_name=\"my-agent\")` is initialized\n- **WHEN** the base URL is constructed\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `http://router:9000/v1/namespaces/default/agent-runtimes/my-agent/invocations/`\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient bootstrap session ID\nThe system SHALL bootstrap session ID by GETting the base invocation URL and reading `x-agentcube-session-id` header.\n\n#### Scenario: Bootstrap session ID from GET request\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is initialized without session_id\n- **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL GET `self.base_url` and extract the `x-agentcube-session-id` header from the response\n\n#### Scenario: Bootstrap fails with missing header\n- **GIVEN** the GET request to bootstrap succeeds but `x-agentcube-session-id` header is missing\n- **WHEN** the response is processed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message `Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id`\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient invoke with POST\nThe system SHALL POST JSON payloads to the base invocation URL with session header and Content-Type.\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke with JSON payload\n- **GIVEN** `invoke(session_id=\"session-abc\", payload={\"input\": \"data\"})` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** the system SHALL POST to `self.base_url` with headers `x-agentcube-session-id: session-abc` and `Content-Type: application/json`, and JSON body `{\"input\": \"data\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke with timeout tuple\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)` is initialized\n- **WHEN** `invoke(session_id=\"session-abc\", payload={}, timeout=None)` is called\n- **THEN** the request timeout SHALL be `(5.0, 120)`\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke without session ID raises error\n- **GIVEN** `invoke(session_id=\"\", payload={})` is called with falsy session_id\n- **WHEN** the method executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n\n### Requirement: HTTP session management with connection pooling\nThe system SHALL use `requests.Session` with `HTTPAdapter` for connection pooling on all HTTP clients.\n\n#### Scenario: Create session with default pool settings\n- **GIVEN** `create_session()` is called without arguments\n- **WHEN** the session is created\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create `requests.Session`, mount `HTTPAdapter` with `pool_connections=10` and `pool_maxsize=10` for both `http://` and `https://`, and return the session\n\n#### Scenario: Create session with custom pool settings\n- **GIVEN** `create_session(pool_connections=20, pool_maxsize=20)` is called\n- **WHEN** the session is created\n- **THEN** the system SHALL mount `HTTPAdapter` with the custom pool values\n\n#### Scenario: Closing sessions releases connections\n- **GIVEN** a client has an active `requests.Session`\n- **WHEN** `close()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `self.session.close()` to properly close the session and release connections\n\n### Requirement: Context manager support for HTTP clients\nThe system SHALL support context manager protocol via `__enter__` and `__exit__` for proper resource cleanup.\n\n#### Scenario: Control plane client context manager\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` is used in a `with` block\n- **WHEN** the block exits\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `close()` to close the HTTP session\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient context manager\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is used in a `with` block\n- **WHEN** the block exits\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `close()` to close the HTTP session\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient context manager\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is used in a `with` block\n- **WHEN** the block exits\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `close()` to close the HTTP session\n\n### Requirement: Exception hierarchy for HTTP operations\nThe system SHALL define `AgentCubeError` as base exception, with `SessionError` and `DataPlaneError` for HTTP client operations.\n\n#### Scenario: SessionError for control plane failures\n- **GIVEN** a control plane operation fails\n- **WHEN** the error is raised\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `SessionError` (subclass of `AgentCubeError`)\n\n#### Scenario: DataPlaneError for data plane failures\n- **GIVEN** a data plane operation fails\n- **WHEN** the error is raised\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `DataPlaneError` (subclass of `AgentCubeError`)\n\n### Requirement: Token file reading utility\nThe system SHALL provide `read_token_from_file` utility to read Kubernetes service account tokens.\n\n#### Scenario: Read existing token file\n- **GIVEN** `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` contains token content with newline\n- **WHEN** `read_token_from_file(\"/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token\")` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return the token content stripped of whitespace\n\n#### Scenario: Token file missing returns empty string\n- **GIVEN** the token file does not exist\n- **WHEN** `read_token_from_file(\"/nonexistent/token\")` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return empty string without raising exception\n\n### Requirement: Logger configuration utility\nThe system SHALL provide `get_logger` utility for consistent logger configuration.\n\n#### Scenario: Logger with default INFO level\n- **GIVEN** `get_logger(\"agentcube.client\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the logger is created\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return a `logging.Logger` instance with name `\"agentcube.client\"` and level `logging.INFO`\n\n#### Scenario: Logger with custom level\n- **GIVEN** `get_logger(\"agentcube.client\", level=logging.DEBUG)` is called\n- **WHEN** the logger is created\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return a logger with level set to `logging.DEBUG`","oldString":"## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreterClient initialization with environment variable resolution\nThe system SHALL resolve `workload_manager_url` from parameter or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` environment variable, resolve `router_url` from parameter or `ROUTER_URL` environment variable (required), and resolve `auth_token` from parameter or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`.\n\n#### Scenario: All parameters provided explicitly\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(name=\"test\", namespace=\"dev\", ttl=1800, workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\", router_url=\"http://router:9000\", auth_token=\"custom-token\")` is called\n- **WHEN** initialization completes\n- **THEN** the client SHALL use the provided `workload_manager_url`, `router_url`, and `auth_token` values directly\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager URL from environment\n- **GIVEN** environment variable `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` is set to `http://wm-default:8080`\n- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(router_url=\"http://router:9000\")` is called without `workload_manager_url`\n- **THEN** the client SHALL resolve `workload_manager_url` to `http://wm-default:8080`\n\n#### Scenario: Router URL missing required parameter\n- **GIVEN** neither `router_url` parameter nor `ROUTER_URL` environment variable is set\n- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient()` is initialized\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message containing \"Router URL must be provided\"\n\n#### Scenario: Auth token from Kubernetes service account\n- **GIVEN** `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` contains valid JWT token\n- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient()` is called without `auth_token` parameter\n- **THEN** the client SHALL read and use the token from the file path via `read_token_from_file`\n\n#### Scenario: Service account token file missing\n- **GIVEN** `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` does not exist\n- **WHEN** `auth_token` is not provided and `read_token_from_file` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return empty string and `auth_token` SHALL be set to `None` (no Authorization header will be set)\n\n### Requirement: Session lifecycle with context manager support\nThe system SHALL support context manager protocol via `__enter__` and `__exit__`, create session via control plane if `session_id` not provided, and cleanup resources on exit.\n\n#### Scenario: Context manager entry with existing session_id\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(session_id=\"existing-session\")` is created\n- **WHEN** the client enters a context manager block via `with client:`\n- **THEN** `__enter__` SHALL return `self` without creating a new session\n\n#### Scenario: Context manager entry creates new session\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient()` is created without `session_id`\n- **WHEN** the client enters a context manager block\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `ControlPlaneClient.create_session()`, set `session_id` to returned value, initialize `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, and return `self`\n\n#### Scenario: Context manager normal exit\n- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterClient` is used in a `with` block and `session_id` was created during entry\n- **WHEN** the block exits normally\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()`, which closes data-plane client, deletes control-plane session via `ControlPlaneClient.delete_session()`, and closes control-plane HTTP session\n\n#### Scenario: Context manager exit with exception\n- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterClient` is used in a `with` block and an exception occurs in the block\n- **WHEN** the block exits with exception\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()` to clean up resources, then re-raise the exception with exception info passed to `__exit__`\n\n#### Scenario: Manual stop after context manager\n- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterClient` has already exited its context manager and `stop()` was called\n- **WHEN** `stop()` is called again manually\n- **THEN** subsequent calls SHALL be idempotent and not raise errors\n\n### Requirement: Data plane initialization failure handling\nThe system SHALL handle data plane initialization failures by cleaning up created sessions before re-raising.\n\n#### Scenario: Data plane init fails after session creation\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` was not provided and `ControlPlaneClient.create_session()` succeeded returning \"new-session-123\"\n- **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises an exception during initialization\n- **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning message, call `ControlPlaneClient.delete_session(\"new-session-123\")`, set `session_id` to `None`, and re-raise the original exception\n\n#### Scenario: Data plane init fails with existing session\n- **GIVEN** `session_id=\"existing-456\"` was provided to constructor\n- **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises an exception\n- **THEN** the client SHALL NOT attempt to delete the session (as it was not created by this client), but SHALL re-raise the exception\n\n### Requirement: Command execution with timeout and error handling\nThe system SHALL execute shell commands via data plane, parse JSON response, handle non-zero exit codes, and support custom timeouts.\n\n#### Scenario: Successful command execution\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is initialized and session is active\n- **WHEN** `execute_command(\"echo 'hello world'\")` is called with default timeout\n- **THEN** the system SHALL POST to `api/execute` with JSON `{\"command\": [\"echo\", \"hello world\"], \"timeout\": \"120s\"}`, wait for response, and return `stdout` from response JSON\n\n#### Scenario: Command with non-zero exit code\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"ls /nonexistent\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the response JSON contains `exit_code: 1` and `stderr: \"No such file or directory\"`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError(exit_code=1, stderr=\"No such file or directory\", command=\"ls /nonexistent\")`\n\n#### Scenario: Custom timeout for command execution\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"sleep 10\", timeout=30.0)` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is prepared\n- **THEN** the body SHALL include `timeout: \"30s\"` and the HTTP read timeout SHALL be `32.0` seconds (30 + 2.0 buffer)\n\n#### Scenario: Command timeout without custom override\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"long-running-command\")` is called without timeout parameter\n- **WHEN** the default timeout is applied\n- **THEN** the body SHALL include `timeout: \"120s\"` (from `self.timeout`) and read timeout SHALL be `122.0` seconds\n\n#### Scenario: Command with list argument format\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command([\"ls\", \"-la\", \"/tmp\"])` is called with list of strings\n- **WHEN** the command is executed\n- **THEN** the data plane SHALL receive the list directly in the JSON body `{\"command\": [\"ls\", \"-la\", \"/tmp\"], \"timeout\": \"120s\"}`\n\n### Requirement: Code execution with language-specific handling\nThe system SHALL support `run_code()` for multiple languages with special handling for Python via file write and execute.\n\n#### Scenario: Python code execution\n- **GIVEN** `run_code(language=\"python\", code=\"print('hello')\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the method executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL generate timestamped filename (e.g., `code_20250411_123456.py`), call `write_file(content=\"print('hello')\", remote_path=\"<filename>\")`, then call `execute_command(f\"python3 {filename}\")` and return result\n\n#### Scenario: Python code with alternative language identifier\n- **GIVEN** `run_code(language=\"py\", code=\"x = 1 + 2; print(x)\")` is called\n- **WHEN** language is detected as Python variant\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use the same file-write-and-execute pattern as `\"python\"` or `\"python3\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Non-Python code execution\n- **GIVEN** `run_code(language=\"bash\", code=\"echo 'hello from bash'\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the language is not a Python variant\n- **THEN** the system SHALL POST directly to data plane `run_code` endpoint with `{\"language\": \"bash\", \"code\": \"echo 'hello from bash'\"}` body\n\n### Requirement: File operations via data plane\nThe system SHALL support write, upload, download, and list file operations with proper encoding and headers.\n\n#### Scenario: Write file with base64 encoding\n- **GIVEN** `write_file(content=\"hello world\", remote_path=\"/tmp/test.txt\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** the system SHALL POST to `api/files` with JSON `{\"content\": \"<base64>\", \"path\": \"/tmp/test.txt\", \"mode\": \"0644\"}` where content is base64-encoded\n\n#### Scenario: Upload file via multipart\n- **GIVEN** `upload_file(local_path=\"/local/file.txt\", remote_path=\"/remote/file.txt\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the multipart request is sent\n- **THEN** the system SHALL POST to `api/files` with `files={'file': open('/local/file.txt', 'rb')}`, `data={'path': '/remote/file.txt', 'mode': '0644'}`, and header `x-agentcube-session-id: <session_id>`\n\n#### Scenario: Download file with streaming\n- **GIVEN** `download_file(remote_path=\"/data/result.json\", local_path=\"./result.json\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the file is downloaded\n- **THEN** the system SHALL GET `api/files/data/result.json` (cleaned path) with `stream=True`, write response content to `./result.json`, and close response after writing\n\n#### Scenario: List files in directory\n- **GIVEN** `list_files(path=\"/home/user\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the request completes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL GET `api/files?path=/home/user` and return the JSON response (typically file listing)\n\n#### Scenario: List files default path\n- **GIVEN** `list_files()` is called without path argument\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use default path `.` and query `api/files?path=.`\n\n### Requirement: HTTP session management and connection pooling\nThe system SHALL use `requests.Session` with `HTTPAdapter` for connection pooling on control plane and data plane clients.\n\n#### Scenario: Create session with default pool settings\n- **GIVEN** `create_session()` is called without arguments\n- **WHEN** the session is created\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create `requests.Session`, mount `HTTPAdapter` with `pool_connections=10` and `pool_maxsize=10` for both `http://` and `https://`, and return the session\n\n#### Scenario: Control plane client with custom pool settings\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(pool_connections=20, pool_maxsize=20)` is initialized\n- **WHEN** the HTTP session is created\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use the custom pool values when calling `create_session()`\n\n#### Scenario: Data plane client uses provided session\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is constructed with all required parameters\n- **WHEN** initialization completes\n- **THEN** the client SHALL create its own HTTP session via `create_session()` with configured pool settings\n\n#### Scenario: Closing sessions\n- **GIVEN** a client has an active `requests.Session`\n- **WHEN** `close()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `self.session.close()` to properly close the session and release connections\n\n### Requirement: Logger configuration\nThe system SHALL configure logging with `get_logger()` utility supporting name and level parameters.\n\n#### Scenario: Logger with default INFO level\n- **GIVEN** `get_logger(\"agentcube.code_interpreter\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the logger is created\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return a `logging.Logger` instance with name `\"agentcube.code_interpreter\"` and level `logging.INFO`\n\n#### Scenario: Logger with custom level\n- **GIVEN** `get_logger(\"agentcube.client\", level=logging.DEBUG)` is called\n- **WHEN** the logger is created\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return a logger with level set to `logging.DEBUG`\n\n#### Scenario: Client initialization sets logger\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(verbose=True)` is initialized\n- **WHEN** the logger is set\n- **THEN** the client SHALL create logger with level based on `verbose` flag (DEBUG if True, INFO if False)\n\n### Requirement: Session header injection for data plane requests\nThe system SHALL inject `x-agentcube-session-id` header into all data plane requests.\n\n#### Scenario: Request includes session header\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(session_id=\"session-abc\")` is initialized\n- **WHEN** any `_request()` method call is made\n- **THEN** the request headers SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: session-abc`\n\n#### Scenario: Multipart upload includes session header\n- **GIVEN** `upload_file()` is called\n- **WHEN** the multipart POST is prepared\n- **THEN** the request SHALL explicitly set `x-agentcube-session-id` header alongside the multipart files and data\n\n#### Scenario: JSON request includes session header\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command()` is called with a JSON body\n- **WHEN** the POST request is sent\n- **THEN** the request SHALL include both `Content-Type: application/json` and `x-agentcube-session-id: <session_id>` headers\n\n### Requirement: Base URL construction for data plane\nThe system SHALL construct data plane base URL from router URL, namespace, and CR name unless explicitly provided.\n\n#### Scenario: Base URL from router and metadata\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(router_url=\"http://router:9000\", namespace=\"default\", cr_name=\"my-interpreter\")` is initialized without `base_url`\n- **WHEN** the base URL is constructed\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `http://router:9000/v1/namespaces/default/code-interpreters/my-interpreter/invocations/`\n\n#### Scenario: Explicit base URL overrides construction\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(base_url=\"http://custom:8080/custom/path/\")` is provided\n- **WHEN** initialization completes\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `http://custom:8080/custom/path/` without any router-based construction\n\n### Requirement: Control plane session creation and deletion\nThe system SHALL create sessions via POST to control plane API and delete via DELETE with 404 tolerance.\n\n#### Scenario: Create session returns session ID\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(base_url=\"http://wm:8080\")` is initialized\n- **WHEN** `create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"dev\", ttl=1800, metadata={\"key\": \"value\"})` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL POST `http://wm:8080/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON body containing all parameters and return the `sessionId` from response\n\n#### Scenario: Create session missing session ID in response\n- **GIVEN** the control plane POST succeeds but response JSON lacks `sessionId` field\n- **WHEN** the response is parsed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating missing `sessionId`\n\n#### Scenario: Delete session success\n- **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session-123\")` is called and server returns 200 or 204\n- **WHEN** the response is processed\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`\n\n#### Scenario: Delete session 404 treated as success\n- **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session-404\")` is called and server returns 404\n- **WHEN** the response is received\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return `True` (session already deleted)\n\n#### Scenario: Delete session other failure\n- **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session-err\")` is called and server returns 500\n- **WHEN** the error occurs\n- **THEN** the method SHALL log the error and return `False`\n\n### Requirement: Verbose mode logging\nThe system SHALL support verbose mode for debug logging across client operations.\n\n#### Scenario: Verbose mode enabled\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(verbose=True)` is initialized\n- **WHEN** operations like command execution or file transfers occur\n- **THEN** the client SHALL log debug-level messages including request details, response status, and timing information\n\n#### Scenario: Verbose mode disabled\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(verbose=False)` is initialized (default)\n- **WHEN** operations occur\n- **THEN** the client SHALL log only INFO-level and above messages (errors, warnings, info)\n\n### Requirement: TTL parameter handling\nThe system SHALL use the TTL parameter when creating sessions for session expiration control.\n\n#### Scenario: Custom TTL for session creation\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(ttl=7200)` is initialized without `session_id`\n- **WHEN** a new session is created via control plane\n- **THEN** the request body SHALL include `ttl: 7200` to set session expiration to 2 hours\n\n#### Scenario: Default TTL when not specified\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient()` is initialized without explicit TTL\n- **WHEN** a new session is created\n- **THEN** the request body SHALL include `ttl: 3600` (default 1 hour)\n\n### Requirement: Namespace parameter propagation\nThe system SHALL propagate namespace parameter through control plane and data plane URL construction.\n\n#### Scenario: Custom namespace in constructor\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(namespace=\"production\")` is initialized\n- **WHEN** session is created and data plane is initialized\n- **THEN** the control plane request SHALL include `namespace: \"production\"` and data plane base URL SHALL include `/namespaces/production/`\n\n#### Scenario: Default namespace\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient()` is initialized without namespace\n- **WHEN** initialization completes\n- **THEN** namespace SHALL default to `\"default\"` in both control plane request and data plane URL\n\n### Requirement: Metadata support in session creation\nThe system SHALL support optional metadata dictionary when creating sessions.\n\n#### Scenario: Session with metadata\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient.create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"dev\", metadata={\"owner\": \"user1\", \"purpose\": \"data-analysis\"})` is called\n- **WHEN** the request body is prepared\n- **THEN** the JSON SHALL include `metadata: {\"owner\": \"user1\", \"purpose\": \"data-analysis\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Session without metadata\n- **GIVEN** `create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"dev\")` is called without metadata parameter\n- **WHEN** the request body is prepared\n- **THEN** the JSON SHALL include `metadata: null` or omit the metadata field"},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"diff":"Index: /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md\n===================================================================\n--- /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md\n+++ /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md\n@@ -12,124 +12,130 @@\n This delta specification defines implementation requirements for the HTTP底层客户端 components in the AgentCube Python SDK, including `ControlPlaneClient`, `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, and `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`. It focuses on HTTP session management, connection pooling, timeout configuration, header management, and exception handling across all HTTP client implementations.\n \n ## Requirements\n \n-### Requirement: CodeInterpreterClient initialization with environment variable resolution\n-The system SHALL resolve `workload_manager_url` from parameter or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` environment variable, resolve `router_url` from parameter or `ROUTER_URL` environment variable (required), and resolve `auth_token` from parameter or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`.\n+### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient initialization with environment variable resolution\n+The system SHALL resolve `base_url` from `workload_manager_url` parameter or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` environment variable, and resolve `auth_token` from parameter or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`.\n \n-#### Scenario: All parameters provided explicitly\n-- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(name=\"test\", namespace=\"dev\", ttl=1800, workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\", router_url=\"http://router:9000\", auth_token=\"custom-token\")` is called\n+#### Scenario: Workload Manager URL from parameter\n+- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\")` is called\n - **WHEN** initialization completes\n-- **THEN** the client SHALL use the provided `workload_manager_url`, `router_url`, and `auth_token` values directly\n+- **THEN** the client SHALL use `http://wm:8080` as `base_url` directly\n \n #### Scenario: Workload Manager URL from environment\n - **GIVEN** environment variable `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` is set to `http://wm-default:8080`\n-- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(router_url=\"http://router:9000\")` is called without `workload_manager_url`\n-- **THEN** the client SHALL resolve `workload_manager_url` to `http://wm-default:8080`\n+- **WHEN** `ControlPlaneClient()` is called without `workload_manager_url`\n+- **THEN** the client SHALL resolve `base_url` to `http://wm-default:8080`\n \n-#### Scenario: Router URL missing required parameter\n-- **GIVEN** neither `router_url` parameter nor `ROUTER_URL` environment variable is set\n-- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient()` is initialized\n-- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message containing \"Router URL must be provided\"\n-\n #### Scenario: Auth token from Kubernetes service account\n - **GIVEN** `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` contains valid JWT token\n-- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient()` is called without `auth_token` parameter\n+- **WHEN** `ControlPlaneClient()` is called without `auth_token` parameter\n - **THEN** the client SHALL read and use the token from the file path via `read_token_from_file`\n \n #### Scenario: Service account token file missing\n - **GIVEN** `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` does not exist\n - **WHEN** `auth_token` is not provided and `read_token_from_file` is called\n-- **THEN** the system SHALL return empty string and `auth_token` SHALL be set to `None` (no Authorization header will be set)\n+- **THEN** the system SHALL return empty string and no `Authorization` header will be set on the session\n \n-### Requirement: Session lifecycle with context manager support\n-The system SHALL support context manager protocol via `__enter__` and `__exit__`, create session via control plane if `session_id` not provided, and cleanup resources on exit.\n+### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient session creation via HTTP POST\n+The system SHALL create sessions by POSTing to `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with proper headers and JSON body.\n \n-#### Scenario: Context manager entry with existing session_id\n-- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(session_id=\"existing-session\")` is created\n-- **WHEN** the client enters a context manager block via `with client:`\n-- **THEN** `__enter__` SHALL return `self` without creating a new session\n+#### Scenario: Create session with all parameters\n+- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(base_url=\"http://wm:8080\")` is initialized\n+- **WHEN** `create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"dev\", ttl=1800, metadata={\"key\": \"value\"})` is called\n+- **THEN** the system SHALL POST `http://wm:8080/v1/code-interpreter` with `Content-Type: application/json`, `Authorization: Bearer {token}` (if token present), and JSON body `{\"name\": \"test\", \"namespace\": \"dev\", \"ttl\": 1800, \"metadata\": {\"key\": \"value\"}}`\n \n-#### Scenario: Context manager entry creates new session\n-- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient()` is created without `session_id`\n-- **WHEN** the client enters a context manager block\n-- **THEN** the system SHALL call `ControlPlaneClient.create_session()`, set `session_id` to returned value, initialize `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, and return `self`\n+#### Scenario: Create session returns session ID\n+- **GIVEN** the control plane POST succeeds with response `{\"sessionId\": \"new-session-123\", ...}`\n+- **WHEN** the response is parsed\n+- **THEN** the method SHALL return `\"new-session-123\"`\n \n-#### Scenario: Context manager normal exit\n-- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterClient` is used in a `with` block and `session_id` was created during entry\n-- **WHEN** the block exits normally\n-- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()`, which closes data-plane client, deletes control-plane session via `ControlPlaneClient.delete_session()`, and closes control-plane HTTP session\n+#### Scenario: Create session missing session ID in response\n+- **GIVEN** the control plane POST succeeds but response JSON lacks `sessionId` field\n+- **WHEN** the response is parsed\n+- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating missing `sessionId`\n \n-#### Scenario: Context manager exit with exception\n-- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterClient` is used in a `with` block and an exception occurs in the block\n-- **WHEN** the block exits with exception\n-- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()` to clean up resources, then re-raise the exception with exception info passed to `__exit__`\n+### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient session deletion via HTTP DELETE with 404 tolerance\n+The system SHALL delete sessions by DELETEing to `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` with 404 treated as success.\n \n-#### Scenario: Manual stop after context manager\n-- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterClient` has already exited its context manager and `stop()` was called\n-- **WHEN** `stop()` is called again manually\n-- **THEN** subsequent calls SHALL be idempotent and not raise errors\n+#### Scenario: Delete session success\n+- **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session-123\")` is called and server returns 200 or 204\n+- **WHEN** the response is processed\n+- **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`\n \n-### Requirement: Data plane initialization failure handling\n-The system SHALL handle data plane initialization failures by cleaning up created sessions before re-raising.\n+#### Scenario: Delete session 404 treated as success\n+- **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session-404\")` is called and server returns 404\n+- **WHEN** the response is received\n+- **THEN** the method SHALL return `True` (session already deleted)\n \n-#### Scenario: Data plane init fails after session creation\n-- **GIVEN** `session_id` was not provided and `ControlPlaneClient.create_session()` succeeded returning \"new-session-123\"\n-- **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises an exception during initialization\n-- **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning message, call `ControlPlaneClient.delete_session(\"new-session-123\")`, set `session_id` to `None`, and re-raise the original exception\n+#### Scenario: Delete session other failure\n+- **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session-err\")` is called and server returns 500\n+- **WHEN** the error occurs\n+- **THEN** the method SHALL log the error and return `False`\n \n-#### Scenario: Data plane init fails with existing session\n-- **GIVEN** `session_id=\"existing-456\"` was provided to constructor\n-- **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises an exception\n-- **THEN** the client SHALL NOT attempt to delete the session (as it was not created by this client), but SHALL re-raise the exception\n+### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient timeout and connection pooling configuration\n+The system SHALL use configurable timeouts and connection pooling via `HTTPAdapter`.\n \n-### Requirement: Command execution with timeout and error handling\n-The system SHALL execute shell commands via data plane, parse JSON response, handle non-zero exit codes, and support custom timeouts.\n+#### Scenario: Default timeout and pool settings\n+- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient()` is initialized without timeout parameters\n+- **WHEN** requests are made\n+- **THEN** the system SHALL use `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, and `pool_maxsize=10`\n \n-#### Scenario: Successful command execution\n-- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is initialized and session is active\n-- **WHEN** `execute_command(\"echo 'hello world'\")` is called with default timeout\n-- **THEN** the system SHALL POST to `api/execute` with JSON `{\"command\": [\"echo\", \"hello world\"], \"timeout\": \"120s\"}`, wait for response, and return `stdout` from response JSON\n+#### Scenario: Custom timeout and pool settings\n+- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(timeout=300, connect_timeout=10.0, pool_connections=20, pool_maxsize=20)` is initialized\n+- **WHEN** requests are made\n+- **THEN** the system SHALL use the custom values for timeouts and connection pooling\n \n-#### Scenario: Command with non-zero exit code\n-- **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"ls /nonexistent\")` is called\n-- **WHEN** the response JSON contains `exit_code: 1` and `stderr: \"No such file or directory\"`\n-- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError(exit_code=1, stderr=\"No such file or directory\", command=\"ls /nonexistent\")`\n+#### Scenario: Timeout tuple applied to requests\n+- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)` is initialized\n+- **WHEN** any HTTP request is made\n+- **THEN** the request timeout SHALL be `(5.0, 120)` (connect, read)\n \n-#### Scenario: Custom timeout for command execution\n-- **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"sleep 10\", timeout=30.0)` is called\n-- **WHEN** the request is prepared\n-- **THEN** the body SHALL include `timeout: \"30s\"` and the HTTP read timeout SHALL be `32.0` seconds (30 + 2.0 buffer)\n+### Requirement: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient base URL construction\n+The system SHALL construct base URL from router URL, namespace, and CR name unless explicitly provided.\n \n-#### Scenario: Command timeout without custom override\n-- **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"long-running-command\")` is called without timeout parameter\n-- **WHEN** the default timeout is applied\n-- **THEN** the body SHALL include `timeout: \"120s\"` (from `self.timeout`) and read timeout SHALL be `122.0` seconds\n+#### Scenario: Base URL from router and metadata\n+- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(router_url=\"http://router:9000\", namespace=\"default\", cr_name=\"my-interpreter\")` is initialized without `base_url`\n+- **WHEN** the base URL is constructed\n+- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `http://router:9000/v1/namespaces/default/code-interpreters/my-interpreter/invocations/`\n \n-#### Scenario: Command with list argument format\n-- **GIVEN** `execute_command([\"ls\", \"-la\", \"/tmp\"])` is called with list of strings\n-- **WHEN** the command is executed\n-- **THEN** the data plane SHALL receive the list directly in the JSON body `{\"command\": [\"ls\", \"-la\", \"/tmp\"], \"timeout\": \"120s\"}`\n+#### Scenario: Explicit base URL overrides construction\n+- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(base_url=\"http://custom:8080/custom/path/\")` is provided\n+- **WHEN** initialization completes\n+- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `http://custom:8080/custom/path/` without any router-based construction\n \n-### Requirement: Code execution with language-specific handling\n-The system SHALL support `run_code()` for multiple languages with special handling for Python via file write and execute.\n+### Requirement: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient session header injection\n+The system SHALL inject `x-agentcube-session-id` header into all requests using lowercase header name.\n \n-#### Scenario: Python code execution\n-- **GIVEN** `run_code(language=\"python\", code=\"print('hello')\")` is called\n-- **WHEN** the method executes\n-- **THEN** the system SHALL generate timestamped filename (e.g., `code_20250411_123456.py`), call `write_file(content=\"print('hello')\", remote_path=\"<filename>\")`, then call `execute_command(f\"python3 {filename}\")` and return result\n+#### Scenario: Request includes session header\n+- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(session_id=\"session-abc\")` is initialized\n+- **WHEN** any `_request()` method call is made\n+- **THEN** the request headers SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: session-abc`\n \n-#### Scenario: Python code with alternative language identifier\n-- **GIVEN** `run_code(language=\"py\", code=\"x = 1 + 2; print(x)\")` is called\n-- **WHEN** language is detected as Python variant\n-- **THEN** the system SHALL use the same file-write-and-execute pattern as `\"python\"` or `\"python3\"`\n+#### Scenario: Multipart upload includes session header\n+- **GIVEN** `upload_file()` is called\n+- **WHEN** the multipart POST is prepared\n+- **THEN** the request SHALL explicitly set `x-agentcube-session-id` header alongside the multipart files and data\n \n-#### Scenario: Non-Python code execution\n-- **GIVEN** `run_code(language=\"bash\", code=\"echo 'hello from bash'\")` is called\n-- **WHEN** the language is not a Python variant\n-- **THEN** the system SHALL POST directly to data plane `run_code` endpoint with `{\"language\": \"bash\", \"code\": \"echo 'hello from bash'\"}` body\n+#### Scenario: JSON request includes session header\n+- **GIVEN** `execute_command()` is called with a JSON body\n+- **WHEN** the POST request is sent\n+- **THEN** the request SHALL include both `Content-Type: application/json` and `x-agentcube-session-id: <session_id>` headers\n \n-### Requirement: File operations via data plane\n+### Requirement: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient execute command with timeout buffer\n+The system SHALL POST to `api/execute` with JSON body and apply read timeout buffer to avoid premature ReadTimeout.\n+\n+#### Scenario: Execute command with default timeout\n+- **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"echo hello\")` is called without timeout parameter\n+- **WHEN** the request is prepared\n+- **THEN** the body SHALL be `{\"command\": [\"echo\", \"hello\"], \"timeout\": \"120s\"}` and HTTP read timeout SHALL be `122.0` seconds (120 + 2.0 buffer)\n+\n+#### Scenario: Execute command with custom timeout\n+- **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"sleep 10\", timeout=30.0)` is called\n+- **WHEN** the request is prepared\n+- **THEN** the body SHALL include `timeout: \"30s\"` and the HTTP read timeout SHALL be `32.0` seconds (30 + 2.0 buffer)\n+\n+### Requirement: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient file operations\n The system SHALL support write, upload, download, and list file operations with proper encoding and headers.\n \n #### Scenario: Write file with base64 encoding\n - **GIVEN** `write_file(content=\"hello world\", remote_path=\"/tmp/test.txt\")` is called\n@@ -148,167 +154,124 @@\n \n #### Scenario: List files in directory\n - **GIVEN** `list_files(path=\"/home/user\")` is called\n - **WHEN** the request completes\n-- **THEN** the system SHALL GET `api/files?path=/home/user` and return the JSON response (typically file listing)\n+- **THEN** the system SHALL GET `api/files?path=/home/user` and return the JSON response\n \n-#### Scenario: List files default path\n-- **GIVEN** `list_files()` is called without path argument\n+### Requirement: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient base URL construction\n+The system SHALL construct base URL from router URL, namespace, and agent name.\n+\n+#### Scenario: Base URL from router and agent metadata\n+- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(router_url=\"http://router:9000\", namespace=\"default\", agent_name=\"my-agent\")` is initialized\n+- **WHEN** the base URL is constructed\n+- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `http://router:9000/v1/namespaces/default/agent-runtimes/my-agent/invocations/`\n+\n+### Requirement: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient bootstrap session ID\n+The system SHALL bootstrap session ID by GETting the base invocation URL and reading `x-agentcube-session-id` header.\n+\n+#### Scenario: Bootstrap session ID from GET request\n+- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is initialized without session_id\n+- **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` is called\n+- **THEN** the system SHALL GET `self.base_url` and extract the `x-agentcube-session-id` header from the response\n+\n+#### Scenario: Bootstrap fails with missing header\n+- **GIVEN** the GET request to bootstrap succeeds but `x-agentcube-session-id` header is missing\n+- **WHEN** the response is processed\n+- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message `Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id`\n+\n+### Requirement: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient invoke with POST\n+The system SHALL POST JSON payloads to the base invocation URL with session header and Content-Type.\n+\n+#### Scenario: Invoke with JSON payload\n+- **GIVEN** `invoke(session_id=\"session-abc\", payload={\"input\": \"data\"})` is called\n - **WHEN** the request is sent\n-- **THEN** the system SHALL use default path `.` and query `api/files?path=.`\n+- **THEN** the system SHALL POST to `self.base_url` with headers `x-agentcube-session-id: session-abc` and `Content-Type: application/json`, and JSON body `{\"input\": \"data\"}`\n \n-### Requirement: HTTP session management and connection pooling\n-The system SHALL use `requests.Session` with `HTTPAdapter` for connection pooling on control plane and data plane clients.\n+#### Scenario: Invoke with timeout tuple\n+- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)` is initialized\n+- **WHEN** `invoke(session_id=\"session-abc\", payload={}, timeout=None)` is called\n+- **THEN** the request timeout SHALL be `(5.0, 120)`\n \n+#### Scenario: Invoke without session ID raises error\n+- **GIVEN** `invoke(session_id=\"\", payload={})` is called with falsy session_id\n+- **WHEN** the method executes\n+- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n+\n+### Requirement: HTTP session management with connection pooling\n+The system SHALL use `requests.Session` with `HTTPAdapter` for connection pooling on all HTTP clients.\n+\n #### Scenario: Create session with default pool settings\n - **GIVEN** `create_session()` is called without arguments\n - **WHEN** the session is created\n - **THEN** the system SHALL create `requests.Session`, mount `HTTPAdapter` with `pool_connections=10` and `pool_maxsize=10` for both `http://` and `https://`, and return the session\n \n-#### Scenario: Control plane client with custom pool settings\n-- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(pool_connections=20, pool_maxsize=20)` is initialized\n-- **WHEN** the HTTP session is created\n-- **THEN** the system SHALL use the custom pool values when calling `create_session()`\n+#### Scenario: Create session with custom pool settings\n+- **GIVEN** `create_session(pool_connections=20, pool_maxsize=20)` is called\n+- **WHEN** the session is created\n+- **THEN** the system SHALL mount `HTTPAdapter` with the custom pool values\n \n-#### Scenario: Data plane client uses provided session\n-- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is constructed with all required parameters\n-- **WHEN** initialization completes\n-- **THEN** the client SHALL create its own HTTP session via `create_session()` with configured pool settings\n-\n-#### Scenario: Closing sessions\n+#### Scenario: Closing sessions releases connections\n - **GIVEN** a client has an active `requests.Session`\n - **WHEN** `close()` is called\n - **THEN** the system SHALL call `self.session.close()` to properly close the session and release connections\n \n-### Requirement: Logger configuration\n-The system SHALL configure logging with `get_logger()` utility supporting name and level parameters.\n+### Requirement: Context manager support for HTTP clients\n+The system SHALL support context manager protocol via `__enter__` and `__exit__` for proper resource cleanup.\n \n-#### Scenario: Logger with default INFO level\n-- **GIVEN** `get_logger(\"agentcube.code_interpreter\")` is called\n-- **WHEN** the logger is created\n-- **THEN** the system SHALL return a `logging.Logger` instance with name `\"agentcube.code_interpreter\"` and level `logging.INFO`\n+#### Scenario: Control plane client context manager\n+- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` is used in a `with` block\n+- **WHEN** the block exits\n+- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `close()` to close the HTTP session\n \n-#### Scenario: Logger with custom level\n-- **GIVEN** `get_logger(\"agentcube.client\", level=logging.DEBUG)` is called\n-- **WHEN** the logger is created\n-- **THEN** the system SHALL return a logger with level set to `logging.DEBUG`\n+#### Scenario: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient context manager\n+- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is used in a `with` block\n+- **WHEN** the block exits\n+- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `close()` to close the HTTP session\n \n-#### Scenario: Client initialization sets logger\n-- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(verbose=True)` is initialized\n-- **WHEN** the logger is set\n-- **THEN** the client SHALL create logger with level based on `verbose` flag (DEBUG if True, INFO if False)\n+#### Scenario: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient context manager\n+- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is used in a `with` block\n+- **WHEN** the block exits\n+- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `close()` to close the HTTP session\n \n-### Requirement: Session header injection for data plane requests\n-The system SHALL inject `x-agentcube-session-id` header into all data plane requests.\n+### Requirement: Exception hierarchy for HTTP operations\n+The system SHALL define `AgentCubeError` as base exception, with `SessionError` and `DataPlaneError` for HTTP client operations.\n \n-#### Scenario: Request includes session header\n-- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(session_id=\"session-abc\")` is initialized\n-- **WHEN** any `_request()` method call is made\n-- **THEN** the request headers SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: session-abc`\n+#### Scenario: SessionError for control plane failures\n+- **GIVEN** a control plane operation fails\n+- **WHEN** the error is raised\n+- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `SessionError` (subclass of `AgentCubeError`)\n \n-#### Scenario: Multipart upload includes session header\n-- **GIVEN** `upload_file()` is called\n-- **WHEN** the multipart POST is prepared\n-- **THEN** the request SHALL explicitly set `x-agentcube-session-id` header alongside the multipart files and data\n+#### Scenario: DataPlaneError for data plane failures\n+- **GIVEN** a data plane operation fails\n+- **WHEN** the error is raised\n+- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `DataPlaneError` (subclass of `AgentCubeError`)\n \n-#### Scenario: JSON request includes session header\n-- **GIVEN** `execute_command()` is called with a JSON body\n-- **WHEN** the POST request is sent\n-- **THEN** the request SHALL include both `Content-Type: application/json` and `x-agentcube-session-id: <session_id>` headers\n+### Requirement: Token file reading utility\n+The system SHALL provide `read_token_from_file` utility to read Kubernetes service account tokens.\n \n-### Requirement: Base URL construction for data plane\n-The system SHALL construct data plane base URL from router URL, namespace, and CR name unless explicitly provided.\n+#### Scenario: Read existing token file\n+- **GIVEN** `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` contains token content with newline\n+- **WHEN** `read_token_from_file(\"/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token\")` is called\n+- **THEN** the system SHALL return the token content stripped of whitespace\n \n-#### Scenario: Base URL from router and metadata\n-- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(router_url=\"http://router:9000\", namespace=\"default\", cr_name=\"my-interpreter\")` is initialized without `base_url`\n-- **WHEN** the base URL is constructed\n-- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `http://router:9000/v1/namespaces/default/code-interpreters/my-interpreter/invocations/`\n+#### Scenario: Token file missing returns empty string\n+- **GIVEN** the token file does not exist\n+- **WHEN** `read_token_from_file(\"/nonexistent/token\")` is called\n+- **THEN** the system SHALL return empty string without raising exception\n \n-#### Scenario: Explicit base URL overrides construction\n-- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(base_url=\"http://custom:8080/custom/path/\")` is provided\n-- **WHEN** initialization completes\n-- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `http://custom:8080/custom/path/` without any router-based construction\n+### Requirement: Logger configuration utility\n+The system SHALL provide `get_logger` utility for consistent logger configuration.\n \n-### Requirement: Control plane session creation and deletion\n-The system SHALL create sessions via POST to control plane API and delete via DELETE with 404 tolerance.\n+#### Scenario: Logger with default INFO level\n+- **GIVEN** `get_logger(\"agentcube.client\")` is called\n+- **WHEN** the logger is created\n+- **THEN** the system SHALL return a `logging.Logger` instance with name `\"agentcube.client\"` and level `logging.INFO`\n \n-#### Scenario: Create session returns session ID\n-- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(base_url=\"http://wm:8080\")` is initialized\n-- **WHEN** `create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"dev\", ttl=1800, metadata={\"key\": \"value\"})` is called\n-- **THEN** the system SHALL POST `http://wm:8080/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON body containing all parameters and return the `sessionId` from response\n+#### Scenario: Logger with custom level\n+- **GIVEN** `get_logger(\"agentcube.client\", level=logging.DEBUG)` is called\n+- **WHEN** the logger is created\n+- **THEN** the system SHALL return a logger with level set to `logging.DEBUG`\n \n-#### Scenario: Create session missing session ID in response\n-- **GIVEN** the control plane POST succeeds but response JSON lacks `sessionId` field\n-- **WHEN** the response is parsed\n-- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating missing `sessionId`\n-\n-#### Scenario: Delete session success\n-- **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session-123\")` is called and server returns 200 or 204\n-- **WHEN** the response is processed\n-- **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`\n-\n-#### Scenario: Delete session 404 treated as success\n-- **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session-404\")` is called and server returns 404\n-- **WHEN** the response is received\n-- **THEN** the method SHALL return `True` (session already deleted)\n-\n-#### Scenario: Delete session other failure\n-- **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session-err\")` is called and server returns 500\n-- **WHEN** the error occurs\n-- **THEN** the method SHALL log the error and return `False`\n-\n-### Requirement: Verbose mode logging\n-The system SHALL support verbose mode for debug logging across client operations.\n-\n-#### Scenario: Verbose mode enabled\n-- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(verbose=True)` is initialized\n-- **WHEN** operations like command execution or file transfers occur\n-- **THEN** the client SHALL log debug-level messages including request details, response status, and timing information\n-\n-#### Scenario: Verbose mode disabled\n-- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(verbose=False)` is initialized (default)\n-- **WHEN** operations occur\n-- **THEN** the client SHALL log only INFO-level and above messages (errors, warnings, info)\n-\n-### Requirement: TTL parameter handling\n-The system SHALL use the TTL parameter when creating sessions for session expiration control.\n-\n-#### Scenario: Custom TTL for session creation\n-- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(ttl=7200)` is initialized without `session_id`\n-- **WHEN** a new session is created via control plane\n-- **THEN** the request body SHALL include `ttl: 7200` to set session expiration to 2 hours\n-\n-#### Scenario: Default TTL when not specified\n-- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient()` is initialized without explicit TTL\n-- **WHEN** a new session is created\n-- **THEN** the request body SHALL include `ttl: 3600` (default 1 hour)\n-\n-### Requirement: Namespace parameter propagation\n-The system SHALL propagate namespace parameter through control plane and data plane URL construction.\n-\n-#### Scenario: Custom namespace in constructor\n-- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(namespace=\"production\")` is initialized\n-- **WHEN** session is created and data plane is initialized\n-- **THEN** the control plane request SHALL include `namespace: \"production\"` and data plane base URL SHALL include `/namespaces/production/`\n-\n-#### Scenario: Default namespace\n-- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient()` is initialized without namespace\n-- **WHEN** initialization completes\n-- **THEN** namespace SHALL default to `\"default\"` in both control plane request and data plane URL\n-\n-### Requirement: Metadata support in session creation\n-The system SHALL support optional metadata dictionary when creating sessions.\n-\n-#### Scenario: Session with metadata\n-- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient.create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"dev\", metadata={\"owner\": \"user1\", \"purpose\": \"data-analysis\"})` is called\n-- **WHEN** the request body is prepared\n-- **THEN** the JSON SHALL include `metadata: {\"owner\": \"user1\", \"purpose\": \"data-analysis\"}`\n-\n-#### Scenario: Session without metadata\n-- **GIVEN** `create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"dev\")` is called without metadata parameter\n-- **WHEN** the request body is prepared\n-- **THEN** the JSON SHALL include `metadata: null` or omit the metadata field\n-\n ## Acceptance Criteria Summary\n \n 1. ✅ Client initialization resolves environment variables correctly\n 2. ✅ Context manager protocol properly manages lifecycle\n","filediff":{"file":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md","before":"# Delta Specification: AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n\n## AR Metadata\n- **AR ID**: AR-029\n- **Title**: SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n- **Module**: sdk-python\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Status**: Implementation Required\n\n## Purpose\nThis delta specification defines implementation requirements for the HTTP底层客户端 components in the AgentCube Python SDK, including `ControlPlaneClient`, `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, and `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`. It focuses on HTTP session management, connection pooling, timeout configuration, header management, and exception handling across all HTTP client implementations.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreterClient initialization with environment variable resolution\nThe system SHALL resolve `workload_manager_url` from parameter or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` environment variable, resolve `router_url` from parameter or `ROUTER_URL` environment variable (required), and resolve `auth_token` from parameter or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`.\n\n#### Scenario: All parameters provided explicitly\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(name=\"test\", namespace=\"dev\", ttl=1800, workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\", router_url=\"http://router:9000\", auth_token=\"custom-token\")` is called\n- **WHEN** initialization completes\n- **THEN** the client SHALL use the provided `workload_manager_url`, `router_url`, and `auth_token` values directly\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager URL from environment\n- **GIVEN** environment variable `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` is set to `http://wm-default:8080`\n- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(router_url=\"http://router:9000\")` is called without `workload_manager_url`\n- **THEN** the client SHALL resolve `workload_manager_url` to `http://wm-default:8080`\n\n#### Scenario: Router URL missing required parameter\n- **GIVEN** neither `router_url` parameter nor `ROUTER_URL` environment variable is set\n- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient()` is initialized\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message containing \"Router URL must be provided\"\n\n#### Scenario: Auth token from Kubernetes service account\n- **GIVEN** `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` contains valid JWT token\n- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient()` is called without `auth_token` parameter\n- **THEN** the client SHALL read and use the token from the file path via `read_token_from_file`\n\n#### Scenario: Service account token file missing\n- **GIVEN** `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` does not exist\n- **WHEN** `auth_token` is not provided and `read_token_from_file` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return empty string and `auth_token` SHALL be set to `None` (no Authorization header will be set)\n\n### Requirement: Session lifecycle with context manager support\nThe system SHALL support context manager protocol via `__enter__` and `__exit__`, create session via control plane if `session_id` not provided, and cleanup resources on exit.\n\n#### Scenario: Context manager entry with existing session_id\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(session_id=\"existing-session\")` is created\n- **WHEN** the client enters a context manager block via `with client:`\n- **THEN** `__enter__` SHALL return `self` without creating a new session\n\n#### Scenario: Context manager entry creates new session\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient()` is created without `session_id`\n- **WHEN** the client enters a context manager block\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `ControlPlaneClient.create_session()`, set `session_id` to returned value, initialize `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, and return `self`\n\n#### Scenario: Context manager normal exit\n- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterClient` is used in a `with` block and `session_id` was created during entry\n- **WHEN** the block exits normally\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()`, which closes data-plane client, deletes control-plane session via `ControlPlaneClient.delete_session()`, and closes control-plane HTTP session\n\n#### Scenario: Context manager exit with exception\n- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterClient` is used in a `with` block and an exception occurs in the block\n- **WHEN** the block exits with exception\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()` to clean up resources, then re-raise the exception with exception info passed to `__exit__`\n\n#### Scenario: Manual stop after context manager\n- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterClient` has already exited its context manager and `stop()` was called\n- **WHEN** `stop()` is called again manually\n- **THEN** subsequent calls SHALL be idempotent and not raise errors\n\n### Requirement: Data plane initialization failure handling\nThe system SHALL handle data plane initialization failures by cleaning up created sessions before re-raising.\n\n#### Scenario: Data plane init fails after session creation\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` was not provided and `ControlPlaneClient.create_session()` succeeded returning \"new-session-123\"\n- **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises an exception during initialization\n- **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning message, call `ControlPlaneClient.delete_session(\"new-session-123\")`, set `session_id` to `None`, and re-raise the original exception\n\n#### Scenario: Data plane init fails with existing session\n- **GIVEN** `session_id=\"existing-456\"` was provided to constructor\n- **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises an exception\n- **THEN** the client SHALL NOT attempt to delete the session (as it was not created by this client), but SHALL re-raise the exception\n\n### Requirement: Command execution with timeout and error handling\nThe system SHALL execute shell commands via data plane, parse JSON response, handle non-zero exit codes, and support custom timeouts.\n\n#### Scenario: Successful command execution\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is initialized and session is active\n- **WHEN** `execute_command(\"echo 'hello world'\")` is called with default timeout\n- **THEN** the system SHALL POST to `api/execute` with JSON `{\"command\": [\"echo\", \"hello world\"], \"timeout\": \"120s\"}`, wait for response, and return `stdout` from response JSON\n\n#### Scenario: Command with non-zero exit code\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"ls /nonexistent\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the response JSON contains `exit_code: 1` and `stderr: \"No such file or directory\"`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError(exit_code=1, stderr=\"No such file or directory\", command=\"ls /nonexistent\")`\n\n#### Scenario: Custom timeout for command execution\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"sleep 10\", timeout=30.0)` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is prepared\n- **THEN** the body SHALL include `timeout: \"30s\"` and the HTTP read timeout SHALL be `32.0` seconds (30 + 2.0 buffer)\n\n#### Scenario: Command timeout without custom override\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"long-running-command\")` is called without timeout parameter\n- **WHEN** the default timeout is applied\n- **THEN** the body SHALL include `timeout: \"120s\"` (from `self.timeout`) and read timeout SHALL be `122.0` seconds\n\n#### Scenario: Command with list argument format\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command([\"ls\", \"-la\", \"/tmp\"])` is called with list of strings\n- **WHEN** the command is executed\n- **THEN** the data plane SHALL receive the list directly in the JSON body `{\"command\": [\"ls\", \"-la\", \"/tmp\"], \"timeout\": \"120s\"}`\n\n### Requirement: Code execution with language-specific handling\nThe system SHALL support `run_code()` for multiple languages with special handling for Python via file write and execute.\n\n#### Scenario: Python code execution\n- **GIVEN** `run_code(language=\"python\", code=\"print('hello')\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the method executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL generate timestamped filename (e.g., `code_20250411_123456.py`), call `write_file(content=\"print('hello')\", remote_path=\"<filename>\")`, then call `execute_command(f\"python3 {filename}\")` and return result\n\n#### Scenario: Python code with alternative language identifier\n- **GIVEN** `run_code(language=\"py\", code=\"x = 1 + 2; print(x)\")` is called\n- **WHEN** language is detected as Python variant\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use the same file-write-and-execute pattern as `\"python\"` or `\"python3\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Non-Python code execution\n- **GIVEN** `run_code(language=\"bash\", code=\"echo 'hello from bash'\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the language is not a Python variant\n- **THEN** the system SHALL POST directly to data plane `run_code` endpoint with `{\"language\": \"bash\", \"code\": \"echo 'hello from bash'\"}` body\n\n### Requirement: File operations via data plane\nThe system SHALL support write, upload, download, and list file operations with proper encoding and headers.\n\n#### Scenario: Write file with base64 encoding\n- **GIVEN** `write_file(content=\"hello world\", remote_path=\"/tmp/test.txt\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** the system SHALL POST to `api/files` with JSON `{\"content\": \"<base64>\", \"path\": \"/tmp/test.txt\", \"mode\": \"0644\"}` where content is base64-encoded\n\n#### Scenario: Upload file via multipart\n- **GIVEN** `upload_file(local_path=\"/local/file.txt\", remote_path=\"/remote/file.txt\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the multipart request is sent\n- **THEN** the system SHALL POST to `api/files` with `files={'file': open('/local/file.txt', 'rb')}`, `data={'path': '/remote/file.txt', 'mode': '0644'}`, and header `x-agentcube-session-id: <session_id>`\n\n#### Scenario: Download file with streaming\n- **GIVEN** `download_file(remote_path=\"/data/result.json\", local_path=\"./result.json\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the file is downloaded\n- **THEN** the system SHALL GET `api/files/data/result.json` (cleaned path) with `stream=True`, write response content to `./result.json`, and close response after writing\n\n#### Scenario: List files in directory\n- **GIVEN** `list_files(path=\"/home/user\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the request completes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL GET `api/files?path=/home/user` and return the JSON response (typically file listing)\n\n#### Scenario: List files default path\n- **GIVEN** `list_files()` is called without path argument\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use default path `.` and query `api/files?path=.`\n\n### Requirement: HTTP session management and connection pooling\nThe system SHALL use `requests.Session` with `HTTPAdapter` for connection pooling on control plane and data plane clients.\n\n#### Scenario: Create session with default pool settings\n- **GIVEN** `create_session()` is called without arguments\n- **WHEN** the session is created\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create `requests.Session`, mount `HTTPAdapter` with `pool_connections=10` and `pool_maxsize=10` for both `http://` and `https://`, and return the session\n\n#### Scenario: Control plane client with custom pool settings\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(pool_connections=20, pool_maxsize=20)` is initialized\n- **WHEN** the HTTP session is created\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use the custom pool values when calling `create_session()`\n\n#### Scenario: Data plane client uses provided session\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is constructed with all required parameters\n- **WHEN** initialization completes\n- **THEN** the client SHALL create its own HTTP session via `create_session()` with configured pool settings\n\n#### Scenario: Closing sessions\n- **GIVEN** a client has an active `requests.Session`\n- **WHEN** `close()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `self.session.close()` to properly close the session and release connections\n\n### Requirement: Logger configuration\nThe system SHALL configure logging with `get_logger()` utility supporting name and level parameters.\n\n#### Scenario: Logger with default INFO level\n- **GIVEN** `get_logger(\"agentcube.code_interpreter\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the logger is created\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return a `logging.Logger` instance with name `\"agentcube.code_interpreter\"` and level `logging.INFO`\n\n#### Scenario: Logger with custom level\n- **GIVEN** `get_logger(\"agentcube.client\", level=logging.DEBUG)` is called\n- **WHEN** the logger is created\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return a logger with level set to `logging.DEBUG`\n\n#### Scenario: Client initialization sets logger\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(verbose=True)` is initialized\n- **WHEN** the logger is set\n- **THEN** the client SHALL create logger with level based on `verbose` flag (DEBUG if True, INFO if False)\n\n### Requirement: Session header injection for data plane requests\nThe system SHALL inject `x-agentcube-session-id` header into all data plane requests.\n\n#### Scenario: Request includes session header\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(session_id=\"session-abc\")` is initialized\n- **WHEN** any `_request()` method call is made\n- **THEN** the request headers SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: session-abc`\n\n#### Scenario: Multipart upload includes session header\n- **GIVEN** `upload_file()` is called\n- **WHEN** the multipart POST is prepared\n- **THEN** the request SHALL explicitly set `x-agentcube-session-id` header alongside the multipart files and data\n\n#### Scenario: JSON request includes session header\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command()` is called with a JSON body\n- **WHEN** the POST request is sent\n- **THEN** the request SHALL include both `Content-Type: application/json` and `x-agentcube-session-id: <session_id>` headers\n\n### Requirement: Base URL construction for data plane\nThe system SHALL construct data plane base URL from router URL, namespace, and CR name unless explicitly provided.\n\n#### Scenario: Base URL from router and metadata\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(router_url=\"http://router:9000\", namespace=\"default\", cr_name=\"my-interpreter\")` is initialized without `base_url`\n- **WHEN** the base URL is constructed\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `http://router:9000/v1/namespaces/default/code-interpreters/my-interpreter/invocations/`\n\n#### Scenario: Explicit base URL overrides construction\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(base_url=\"http://custom:8080/custom/path/\")` is provided\n- **WHEN** initialization completes\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `http://custom:8080/custom/path/` without any router-based construction\n\n### Requirement: Control plane session creation and deletion\nThe system SHALL create sessions via POST to control plane API and delete via DELETE with 404 tolerance.\n\n#### Scenario: Create session returns session ID\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(base_url=\"http://wm:8080\")` is initialized\n- **WHEN** `create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"dev\", ttl=1800, metadata={\"key\": \"value\"})` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL POST `http://wm:8080/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON body containing all parameters and return the `sessionId` from response\n\n#### Scenario: Create session missing session ID in response\n- **GIVEN** the control plane POST succeeds but response JSON lacks `sessionId` field\n- **WHEN** the response is parsed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating missing `sessionId`\n\n#### Scenario: Delete session success\n- **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session-123\")` is called and server returns 200 or 204\n- **WHEN** the response is processed\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`\n\n#### Scenario: Delete session 404 treated as success\n- **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session-404\")` is called and server returns 404\n- **WHEN** the response is received\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return `True` (session already deleted)\n\n#### Scenario: Delete session other failure\n- **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session-err\")` is called and server returns 500\n- **WHEN** the error occurs\n- **THEN** the method SHALL log the error and return `False`\n\n### Requirement: Verbose mode logging\nThe system SHALL support verbose mode for debug logging across client operations.\n\n#### Scenario: Verbose mode enabled\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(verbose=True)` is initialized\n- **WHEN** operations like command execution or file transfers occur\n- **THEN** the client SHALL log debug-level messages including request details, response status, and timing information\n\n#### Scenario: Verbose mode disabled\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(verbose=False)` is initialized (default)\n- **WHEN** operations occur\n- **THEN** the client SHALL log only INFO-level and above messages (errors, warnings, info)\n\n### Requirement: TTL parameter handling\nThe system SHALL use the TTL parameter when creating sessions for session expiration control.\n\n#### Scenario: Custom TTL for session creation\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(ttl=7200)` is initialized without `session_id`\n- **WHEN** a new session is created via control plane\n- **THEN** the request body SHALL include `ttl: 7200` to set session expiration to 2 hours\n\n#### Scenario: Default TTL when not specified\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient()` is initialized without explicit TTL\n- **WHEN** a new session is created\n- **THEN** the request body SHALL include `ttl: 3600` (default 1 hour)\n\n### Requirement: Namespace parameter propagation\nThe system SHALL propagate namespace parameter through control plane and data plane URL construction.\n\n#### Scenario: Custom namespace in constructor\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(namespace=\"production\")` is initialized\n- **WHEN** session is created and data plane is initialized\n- **THEN** the control plane request SHALL include `namespace: \"production\"` and data plane base URL SHALL include `/namespaces/production/`\n\n#### Scenario: Default namespace\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient()` is initialized without namespace\n- **WHEN** initialization completes\n- **THEN** namespace SHALL default to `\"default\"` in both control plane request and data plane URL\n\n### Requirement: Metadata support in session creation\nThe system SHALL support optional metadata dictionary when creating sessions.\n\n#### Scenario: Session with metadata\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient.create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"dev\", metadata={\"owner\": \"user1\", \"purpose\": \"data-analysis\"})` is called\n- **WHEN** the request body is prepared\n- **THEN** the JSON SHALL include `metadata: {\"owner\": \"user1\", \"purpose\": \"data-analysis\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Session without metadata\n- **GIVEN** `create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"dev\")` is called without metadata parameter\n- **WHEN** the request body is prepared\n- **THEN** the JSON SHALL include `metadata: null` or omit the metadata field\n\n## Acceptance Criteria Summary\n\n1. ✅ Client initialization resolves environment variables correctly\n2. ✅ Context manager protocol properly manages lifecycle\n3. ✅ Data plane failures trigger cleanup before re-raising\n4. ✅ Commands execute with proper timeout and error handling\n5. ✅ Code execution handles Python specially via file operations\n6. ✅ File operations (write, upload, download, list) work correctly\n7. ✅ HTTP sessions use connection pooling\n8. ✅ Logging configured with appropriate levels\n9. ✅ Session headers injected in all data plane requests\n10. ✅ Base URLs constructed correctly for data plane\n11. ✅ Control plane session create/delete work with 404 tolerance\n12. ✅ Verbose mode provides debug logging when enabled\n13. ✅ TTL and namespace parameters propagate correctly\n14. ✅ Optional metadata supported in session creation\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- `requests` library for HTTP client functionality\n- `PyJWT>=2.0.0` for JWT token handling (if needed)\n- `cryptography` for cryptographic operations (if needed)\n- Python >=3.10\n\n## References\n\n- Base Design: `python-sdk/design.md`\n- Base Specification: `python-sdk/spec.md`\n- AR: AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient","after":"# Delta Specification: AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n\n## AR Metadata\n- **AR ID**: AR-029\n- **Title**: SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n- **Module**: sdk-python\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Status**: Implementation Required\n\n## Purpose\nThis delta specification defines implementation requirements for the HTTP底层客户端 components in the AgentCube Python SDK, including `ControlPlaneClient`, `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, and `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`. It focuses on HTTP session management, connection pooling, timeout configuration, header management, and exception handling across all HTTP client implementations.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient initialization with environment variable resolution\nThe system SHALL resolve `base_url` from `workload_manager_url` parameter or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` environment variable, and resolve `auth_token` from parameter or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`.\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager URL from parameter\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\")` is called\n- **WHEN** initialization completes\n- **THEN** the client SHALL use `http://wm:8080` as `base_url` directly\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager URL from environment\n- **GIVEN** environment variable `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` is set to `http://wm-default:8080`\n- **WHEN** `ControlPlaneClient()` is called without `workload_manager_url`\n- **THEN** the client SHALL resolve `base_url` to `http://wm-default:8080`\n\n#### Scenario: Auth token from Kubernetes service account\n- **GIVEN** `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` contains valid JWT token\n- **WHEN** `ControlPlaneClient()` is called without `auth_token` parameter\n- **THEN** the client SHALL read and use the token from the file path via `read_token_from_file`\n\n#### Scenario: Service account token file missing\n- **GIVEN** `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` does not exist\n- **WHEN** `auth_token` is not provided and `read_token_from_file` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return empty string and no `Authorization` header will be set on the session\n\n### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient session creation via HTTP POST\nThe system SHALL create sessions by POSTing to `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with proper headers and JSON body.\n\n#### Scenario: Create session with all parameters\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(base_url=\"http://wm:8080\")` is initialized\n- **WHEN** `create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"dev\", ttl=1800, metadata={\"key\": \"value\"})` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL POST `http://wm:8080/v1/code-interpreter` with `Content-Type: application/json`, `Authorization: Bearer {token}` (if token present), and JSON body `{\"name\": \"test\", \"namespace\": \"dev\", \"ttl\": 1800, \"metadata\": {\"key\": \"value\"}}`\n\n#### Scenario: Create session returns session ID\n- **GIVEN** the control plane POST succeeds with response `{\"sessionId\": \"new-session-123\", ...}`\n- **WHEN** the response is parsed\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return `\"new-session-123\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Create session missing session ID in response\n- **GIVEN** the control plane POST succeeds but response JSON lacks `sessionId` field\n- **WHEN** the response is parsed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating missing `sessionId`\n\n### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient session deletion via HTTP DELETE with 404 tolerance\nThe system SHALL delete sessions by DELETEing to `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` with 404 treated as success.\n\n#### Scenario: Delete session success\n- **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session-123\")` is called and server returns 200 or 204\n- **WHEN** the response is processed\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`\n\n#### Scenario: Delete session 404 treated as success\n- **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session-404\")` is called and server returns 404\n- **WHEN** the response is received\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return `True` (session already deleted)\n\n#### Scenario: Delete session other failure\n- **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session-err\")` is called and server returns 500\n- **WHEN** the error occurs\n- **THEN** the method SHALL log the error and return `False`\n\n### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient timeout and connection pooling configuration\nThe system SHALL use configurable timeouts and connection pooling via `HTTPAdapter`.\n\n#### Scenario: Default timeout and pool settings\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient()` is initialized without timeout parameters\n- **WHEN** requests are made\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, and `pool_maxsize=10`\n\n#### Scenario: Custom timeout and pool settings\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(timeout=300, connect_timeout=10.0, pool_connections=20, pool_maxsize=20)` is initialized\n- **WHEN** requests are made\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use the custom values for timeouts and connection pooling\n\n#### Scenario: Timeout tuple applied to requests\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)` is initialized\n- **WHEN** any HTTP request is made\n- **THEN** the request timeout SHALL be `(5.0, 120)` (connect, read)\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient base URL construction\nThe system SHALL construct base URL from router URL, namespace, and CR name unless explicitly provided.\n\n#### Scenario: Base URL from router and metadata\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(router_url=\"http://router:9000\", namespace=\"default\", cr_name=\"my-interpreter\")` is initialized without `base_url`\n- **WHEN** the base URL is constructed\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `http://router:9000/v1/namespaces/default/code-interpreters/my-interpreter/invocations/`\n\n#### Scenario: Explicit base URL overrides construction\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(base_url=\"http://custom:8080/custom/path/\")` is provided\n- **WHEN** initialization completes\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `http://custom:8080/custom/path/` without any router-based construction\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient session header injection\nThe system SHALL inject `x-agentcube-session-id` header into all requests using lowercase header name.\n\n#### Scenario: Request includes session header\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(session_id=\"session-abc\")` is initialized\n- **WHEN** any `_request()` method call is made\n- **THEN** the request headers SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: session-abc`\n\n#### Scenario: Multipart upload includes session header\n- **GIVEN** `upload_file()` is called\n- **WHEN** the multipart POST is prepared\n- **THEN** the request SHALL explicitly set `x-agentcube-session-id` header alongside the multipart files and data\n\n#### Scenario: JSON request includes session header\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command()` is called with a JSON body\n- **WHEN** the POST request is sent\n- **THEN** the request SHALL include both `Content-Type: application/json` and `x-agentcube-session-id: <session_id>` headers\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient execute command with timeout buffer\nThe system SHALL POST to `api/execute` with JSON body and apply read timeout buffer to avoid premature ReadTimeout.\n\n#### Scenario: Execute command with default timeout\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"echo hello\")` is called without timeout parameter\n- **WHEN** the request is prepared\n- **THEN** the body SHALL be `{\"command\": [\"echo\", \"hello\"], \"timeout\": \"120s\"}` and HTTP read timeout SHALL be `122.0` seconds (120 + 2.0 buffer)\n\n#### Scenario: Execute command with custom timeout\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"sleep 10\", timeout=30.0)` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is prepared\n- **THEN** the body SHALL include `timeout: \"30s\"` and the HTTP read timeout SHALL be `32.0` seconds (30 + 2.0 buffer)\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient file operations\nThe system SHALL support write, upload, download, and list file operations with proper encoding and headers.\n\n#### Scenario: Write file with base64 encoding\n- **GIVEN** `write_file(content=\"hello world\", remote_path=\"/tmp/test.txt\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** the system SHALL POST to `api/files` with JSON `{\"content\": \"<base64>\", \"path\": \"/tmp/test.txt\", \"mode\": \"0644\"}` where content is base64-encoded\n\n#### Scenario: Upload file via multipart\n- **GIVEN** `upload_file(local_path=\"/local/file.txt\", remote_path=\"/remote/file.txt\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the multipart request is sent\n- **THEN** the system SHALL POST to `api/files` with `files={'file': open('/local/file.txt', 'rb')}`, `data={'path': '/remote/file.txt', 'mode': '0644'}`, and header `x-agentcube-session-id: <session_id>`\n\n#### Scenario: Download file with streaming\n- **GIVEN** `download_file(remote_path=\"/data/result.json\", local_path=\"./result.json\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the file is downloaded\n- **THEN** the system SHALL GET `api/files/data/result.json` (cleaned path) with `stream=True`, write response content to `./result.json`, and close response after writing\n\n#### Scenario: List files in directory\n- **GIVEN** `list_files(path=\"/home/user\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the request completes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL GET `api/files?path=/home/user` and return the JSON response\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient base URL construction\nThe system SHALL construct base URL from router URL, namespace, and agent name.\n\n#### Scenario: Base URL from router and agent metadata\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(router_url=\"http://router:9000\", namespace=\"default\", agent_name=\"my-agent\")` is initialized\n- **WHEN** the base URL is constructed\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `http://router:9000/v1/namespaces/default/agent-runtimes/my-agent/invocations/`\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient bootstrap session ID\nThe system SHALL bootstrap session ID by GETting the base invocation URL and reading `x-agentcube-session-id` header.\n\n#### Scenario: Bootstrap session ID from GET request\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is initialized without session_id\n- **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL GET `self.base_url` and extract the `x-agentcube-session-id` header from the response\n\n#### Scenario: Bootstrap fails with missing header\n- **GIVEN** the GET request to bootstrap succeeds but `x-agentcube-session-id` header is missing\n- **WHEN** the response is processed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message `Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id`\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient invoke with POST\nThe system SHALL POST JSON payloads to the base invocation URL with session header and Content-Type.\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke with JSON payload\n- **GIVEN** `invoke(session_id=\"session-abc\", payload={\"input\": \"data\"})` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** the system SHALL POST to `self.base_url` with headers `x-agentcube-session-id: session-abc` and `Content-Type: application/json`, and JSON body `{\"input\": \"data\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke with timeout tuple\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)` is initialized\n- **WHEN** `invoke(session_id=\"session-abc\", payload={}, timeout=None)` is called\n- **THEN** the request timeout SHALL be `(5.0, 120)`\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke without session ID raises error\n- **GIVEN** `invoke(session_id=\"\", payload={})` is called with falsy session_id\n- **WHEN** the method executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n\n### Requirement: HTTP session management with connection pooling\nThe system SHALL use `requests.Session` with `HTTPAdapter` for connection pooling on all HTTP clients.\n\n#### Scenario: Create session with default pool settings\n- **GIVEN** `create_session()` is called without arguments\n- **WHEN** the session is created\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create `requests.Session`, mount `HTTPAdapter` with `pool_connections=10` and `pool_maxsize=10` for both `http://` and `https://`, and return the session\n\n#### Scenario: Create session with custom pool settings\n- **GIVEN** `create_session(pool_connections=20, pool_maxsize=20)` is called\n- **WHEN** the session is created\n- **THEN** the system SHALL mount `HTTPAdapter` with the custom pool values\n\n#### Scenario: Closing sessions releases connections\n- **GIVEN** a client has an active `requests.Session`\n- **WHEN** `close()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `self.session.close()` to properly close the session and release connections\n\n### Requirement: Context manager support for HTTP clients\nThe system SHALL support context manager protocol via `__enter__` and `__exit__` for proper resource cleanup.\n\n#### Scenario: Control plane client context manager\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` is used in a `with` block\n- **WHEN** the block exits\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `close()` to close the HTTP session\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient context manager\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is used in a `with` block\n- **WHEN** the block exits\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `close()` to close the HTTP session\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient context manager\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is used in a `with` block\n- **WHEN** the block exits\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `close()` to close the HTTP session\n\n### Requirement: Exception hierarchy for HTTP operations\nThe system SHALL define `AgentCubeError` as base exception, with `SessionError` and `DataPlaneError` for HTTP client operations.\n\n#### Scenario: SessionError for control plane failures\n- **GIVEN** a control plane operation fails\n- **WHEN** the error is raised\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `SessionError` (subclass of `AgentCubeError`)\n\n#### Scenario: DataPlaneError for data plane failures\n- **GIVEN** a data plane operation fails\n- **WHEN** the error is raised\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `DataPlaneError` (subclass of `AgentCubeError`)\n\n### Requirement: Token file reading utility\nThe system SHALL provide `read_token_from_file` utility to read Kubernetes service account tokens.\n\n#### Scenario: Read existing token file\n- **GIVEN** `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` contains token content with newline\n- **WHEN** `read_token_from_file(\"/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token\")` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return the token content stripped of whitespace\n\n#### Scenario: Token file missing returns empty string\n- **GIVEN** the token file does not exist\n- **WHEN** `read_token_from_file(\"/nonexistent/token\")` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return empty string without raising exception\n\n### Requirement: Logger configuration utility\nThe system SHALL provide `get_logger` utility for consistent logger configuration.\n\n#### Scenario: Logger with default INFO level\n- **GIVEN** `get_logger(\"agentcube.client\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the logger is created\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return a `logging.Logger` instance with name `\"agentcube.client\"` and level `logging.INFO`\n\n#### Scenario: Logger with custom level\n- **GIVEN** `get_logger(\"agentcube.client\", level=logging.DEBUG)` is called\n- **WHEN** the logger is created\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return a logger with level set to `logging.DEBUG`\n\n## Acceptance Criteria Summary\n\n1. ✅ Client initialization resolves environment variables correctly\n2. ✅ Context manager protocol properly manages lifecycle\n3. ✅ Data plane failures trigger cleanup before re-raising\n4. ✅ Commands execute with proper timeout and error handling\n5. ✅ Code execution handles Python specially via file operations\n6. ✅ File operations (write, upload, download, list) work correctly\n7. ✅ HTTP sessions use connection pooling\n8. ✅ Logging configured with appropriate levels\n9. ✅ Session headers injected in all data plane requests\n10. ✅ Base URLs constructed correctly for data plane\n11. ✅ Control plane session create/delete work with 404 tolerance\n12. ✅ Verbose mode provides debug logging when enabled\n13. ✅ TTL and namespace parameters propagate correctly\n14. ✅ Optional metadata supported in session creation\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- `requests` library for HTTP client functionality\n- `PyJWT>=2.0.0` for JWT token handling (if needed)\n- `cryptography` for cryptographic operations (if needed)\n- Python >=3.10\n\n## References\n\n- Base Design: `python-sdk/design.md`\n- Base Specification: `python-sdk/spec.md`\n- AR: AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient","additions":178,"deletions":215},"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775879444382,"end":1775879444490}}}}
