{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879464094,"sessionID":"ses_28558a73bffe63pzmnHs6VtxMQ","part":{"id":"prt_d7aaa246b001n40CDfRq69ca6K","messageID":"msg_d7aa9d854001Z6So7SN61D6gNW","sessionID":"ses_28558a73bffe63pzmnHs6VtxMQ","type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"toolu_tool-754e17a87a3f41588eb5f9f358aff5a5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md","newString":"## Acceptance Criteria Summary\n\n1. ✅ ControlPlaneClient resolves environment variables for base_url and auth_token\n2. ✅ ControlPlaneClient creates sessions via POST with proper headers and JSON body\n3. ✅ ControlPlaneClient deletes sessions via DELETE with 404 tolerance\n4. ✅ ControlPlaneClient uses configurable timeouts and connection pooling\n5. ✅ CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient constructs base URL from router URL, namespace, and CR name\n6. ✅ CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient injects x-agentcube-session-id header in all requests\n7. ✅ CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient executes commands with timeout buffer to avoid ReadTimeout\n8. ✅ CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient supports write, upload, download, and list file operations\n9. ✅ AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient constructs base URL from router URL, namespace, and agent name\n10. ✅ AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient bootstraps session ID via GET request\n11. ✅ AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient invokes workloads via POST with JSON payload\n12. ✅ HTTP session management uses requests.Session with HTTPAdapter for connection pooling\n13. ✅ Context manager support ensures proper resource cleanup\n14. ✅ Exception hierarchy defines AgentCubeError, SessionError, and DataPlaneError\n15. ✅ Token file reading utility reads Kubernetes service account tokens\n16. ✅ Logger configuration utility provides consistent logger setup\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- `requests` library for HTTP client functionality\n- `PyJWT>=2.0.0` for JWT token handling (if needed)\n- `cryptography` for cryptographic operations (if needed)\n- Python >=3.10\n\n## References\n\n- Base Design: `python-sdk/design.md`\n- Base Specification: `python-sdk/spec.md`\n- AR: AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端","oldString":"## Acceptance Criteria Summary\n\n1. ✅ Client initialization resolves environment variables correctly\n2. ✅ Context manager protocol properly manages lifecycle\n3. ✅ Data plane failures trigger cleanup before re-raising\n4. ✅ Commands execute with proper timeout and error handling\n5. ✅ Code execution handles Python specially via file operations\n6. ✅ File operations (write, upload, download, list) work correctly\n7. ✅ HTTP sessions use connection pooling\n8. ✅ Logging configured with appropriate levels\n9. ✅ Session headers injected in all data plane requests\n10. ✅ Base URLs constructed correctly for data plane\n11. ✅ Control plane session create/delete work with 404 tolerance\n12. ✅ Verbose mode provides debug logging when enabled\n13. ✅ TTL and namespace parameters propagate correctly\n14. ✅ Optional metadata supported in session creation\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- `requests` library for HTTP client functionality\n- `PyJWT>=2.0.0` for JWT token handling (if needed)\n- `cryptography` for cryptographic operations (if needed)\n- Python >=3.10\n\n## References\n\n- Base Design: `python-sdk/design.md`\n- Base Specification: `python-sdk/spec.md`\n- AR: AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient"},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"diff":"Index: /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md\n===================================================================\n--- /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md\n+++ /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md\n@@ -272,22 +272,24 @@\n - **THEN** the system SHALL return a logger with level set to `logging.DEBUG`\n \n ## Acceptance Criteria Summary\n \n-1. ✅ Client initialization resolves environment variables correctly\n-2. ✅ Context manager protocol properly manages lifecycle\n-3. ✅ Data plane failures trigger cleanup before re-raising\n-4. ✅ Commands execute with proper timeout and error handling\n-5. ✅ Code execution handles Python specially via file operations\n-6. ✅ File operations (write, upload, download, list) work correctly\n-7. ✅ HTTP sessions use connection pooling\n-8. ✅ Logging configured with appropriate levels\n-9. ✅ Session headers injected in all data plane requests\n-10. ✅ Base URLs constructed correctly for data plane\n-11. ✅ Control plane session create/delete work with 404 tolerance\n-12. ✅ Verbose mode provides debug logging when enabled\n-13. ✅ TTL and namespace parameters propagate correctly\n-14. ✅ Optional metadata supported in session creation\n+1. ✅ ControlPlaneClient resolves environment variables for base_url and auth_token\n+2. ✅ ControlPlaneClient creates sessions via POST with proper headers and JSON body\n+3. ✅ ControlPlaneClient deletes sessions via DELETE with 404 tolerance\n+4. ✅ ControlPlaneClient uses configurable timeouts and connection pooling\n+5. ✅ CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient constructs base URL from router URL, namespace, and CR name\n+6. ✅ CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient injects x-agentcube-session-id header in all requests\n+7. ✅ CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient executes commands with timeout buffer to avoid ReadTimeout\n+8. ✅ CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient supports write, upload, download, and list file operations\n+9. ✅ AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient constructs base URL from router URL, namespace, and agent name\n+10. ✅ AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient bootstraps session ID via GET request\n+11. ✅ AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient invokes workloads via POST with JSON payload\n+12. ✅ HTTP session management uses requests.Session with HTTPAdapter for connection pooling\n+13. ✅ Context manager support ensures proper resource cleanup\n+14. ✅ Exception hierarchy defines AgentCubeError, SessionError, and DataPlaneError\n+15. ✅ Token file reading utility reads Kubernetes service account tokens\n+16. ✅ Logger configuration utility provides consistent logger setup\n \n ## Dependencies\n \n - `requests` library for HTTP client functionality\n@@ -298,5 +300,5 @@\n ## References\n \n - Base Design: `python-sdk/design.md`\n - Base Specification: `python-sdk/spec.md`\n-- AR: AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n\\ No newline at end of file\n+- AR: AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n\\ No newline at end of file\n","filediff":{"file":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md","before":"# Delta Specification: AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n\n## AR Metadata\n- **AR ID**: AR-029\n- **Title**: SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n- **Module**: sdk-python\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Status**: Implementation Required\n\n## Purpose\nThis delta specification defines implementation requirements for the HTTP底层客户端 components in the AgentCube Python SDK, including `ControlPlaneClient`, `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, and `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`. It focuses on HTTP session management, connection pooling, timeout configuration, header management, and exception handling across all HTTP client implementations.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient initialization with environment variable resolution\nThe system SHALL resolve `base_url` from `workload_manager_url` parameter or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` environment variable, and resolve `auth_token` from parameter or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`.\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager URL from parameter\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\")` is called\n- **WHEN** initialization completes\n- **THEN** the client SHALL use `http://wm:8080` as `base_url` directly\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager URL from environment\n- **GIVEN** environment variable `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` is set to `http://wm-default:8080`\n- **WHEN** `ControlPlaneClient()` is called without `workload_manager_url`\n- **THEN** the client SHALL resolve `base_url` to `http://wm-default:8080`\n\n#### Scenario: Auth token from Kubernetes service account\n- **GIVEN** `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` contains valid JWT token\n- **WHEN** `ControlPlaneClient()` is called without `auth_token` parameter\n- **THEN** the client SHALL read and use the token from the file path via `read_token_from_file`\n\n#### Scenario: Service account token file missing\n- **GIVEN** `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` does not exist\n- **WHEN** `auth_token` is not provided and `read_token_from_file` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return empty string and no `Authorization` header will be set on the session\n\n### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient session creation via HTTP POST\nThe system SHALL create sessions by POSTing to `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with proper headers and JSON body.\n\n#### Scenario: Create session with all parameters\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(base_url=\"http://wm:8080\")` is initialized\n- **WHEN** `create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"dev\", ttl=1800, metadata={\"key\": \"value\"})` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL POST `http://wm:8080/v1/code-interpreter` with `Content-Type: application/json`, `Authorization: Bearer {token}` (if token present), and JSON body `{\"name\": \"test\", \"namespace\": \"dev\", \"ttl\": 1800, \"metadata\": {\"key\": \"value\"}}`\n\n#### Scenario: Create session returns session ID\n- **GIVEN** the control plane POST succeeds with response `{\"sessionId\": \"new-session-123\", ...}`\n- **WHEN** the response is parsed\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return `\"new-session-123\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Create session missing session ID in response\n- **GIVEN** the control plane POST succeeds but response JSON lacks `sessionId` field\n- **WHEN** the response is parsed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating missing `sessionId`\n\n### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient session deletion via HTTP DELETE with 404 tolerance\nThe system SHALL delete sessions by DELETEing to `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` with 404 treated as success.\n\n#### Scenario: Delete session success\n- **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session-123\")` is called and server returns 200 or 204\n- **WHEN** the response is processed\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`\n\n#### Scenario: Delete session 404 treated as success\n- **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session-404\")` is called and server returns 404\n- **WHEN** the response is received\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return `True` (session already deleted)\n\n#### Scenario: Delete session other failure\n- **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session-err\")` is called and server returns 500\n- **WHEN** the error occurs\n- **THEN** the method SHALL log the error and return `False`\n\n### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient timeout and connection pooling configuration\nThe system SHALL use configurable timeouts and connection pooling via `HTTPAdapter`.\n\n#### Scenario: Default timeout and pool settings\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient()` is initialized without timeout parameters\n- **WHEN** requests are made\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, and `pool_maxsize=10`\n\n#### Scenario: Custom timeout and pool settings\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(timeout=300, connect_timeout=10.0, pool_connections=20, pool_maxsize=20)` is initialized\n- **WHEN** requests are made\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use the custom values for timeouts and connection pooling\n\n#### Scenario: Timeout tuple applied to requests\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)` is initialized\n- **WHEN** any HTTP request is made\n- **THEN** the request timeout SHALL be `(5.0, 120)` (connect, read)\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient base URL construction\nThe system SHALL construct base URL from router URL, namespace, and CR name unless explicitly provided.\n\n#### Scenario: Base URL from router and metadata\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(router_url=\"http://router:9000\", namespace=\"default\", cr_name=\"my-interpreter\")` is initialized without `base_url`\n- **WHEN** the base URL is constructed\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `http://router:9000/v1/namespaces/default/code-interpreters/my-interpreter/invocations/`\n\n#### Scenario: Explicit base URL overrides construction\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(base_url=\"http://custom:8080/custom/path/\")` is provided\n- **WHEN** initialization completes\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `http://custom:8080/custom/path/` without any router-based construction\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient session header injection\nThe system SHALL inject `x-agentcube-session-id` header into all requests using lowercase header name.\n\n#### Scenario: Request includes session header\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(session_id=\"session-abc\")` is initialized\n- **WHEN** any `_request()` method call is made\n- **THEN** the request headers SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: session-abc`\n\n#### Scenario: Multipart upload includes session header\n- **GIVEN** `upload_file()` is called\n- **WHEN** the multipart POST is prepared\n- **THEN** the request SHALL explicitly set `x-agentcube-session-id` header alongside the multipart files and data\n\n#### Scenario: JSON request includes session header\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command()` is called with a JSON body\n- **WHEN** the POST request is sent\n- **THEN** the request SHALL include both `Content-Type: application/json` and `x-agentcube-session-id: <session_id>` headers\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient execute command with timeout buffer\nThe system SHALL POST to `api/execute` with JSON body and apply read timeout buffer to avoid premature ReadTimeout.\n\n#### Scenario: Execute command with default timeout\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"echo hello\")` is called without timeout parameter\n- **WHEN** the request is prepared\n- **THEN** the body SHALL be `{\"command\": [\"echo\", \"hello\"], \"timeout\": \"120s\"}` and HTTP read timeout SHALL be `122.0` seconds (120 + 2.0 buffer)\n\n#### Scenario: Execute command with custom timeout\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"sleep 10\", timeout=30.0)` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is prepared\n- **THEN** the body SHALL include `timeout: \"30s\"` and the HTTP read timeout SHALL be `32.0` seconds (30 + 2.0 buffer)\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient file operations\nThe system SHALL support write, upload, download, and list file operations with proper encoding and headers.\n\n#### Scenario: Write file with base64 encoding\n- **GIVEN** `write_file(content=\"hello world\", remote_path=\"/tmp/test.txt\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** the system SHALL POST to `api/files` with JSON `{\"content\": \"<base64>\", \"path\": \"/tmp/test.txt\", \"mode\": \"0644\"}` where content is base64-encoded\n\n#### Scenario: Upload file via multipart\n- **GIVEN** `upload_file(local_path=\"/local/file.txt\", remote_path=\"/remote/file.txt\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the multipart request is sent\n- **THEN** the system SHALL POST to `api/files` with `files={'file': open('/local/file.txt', 'rb')}`, `data={'path': '/remote/file.txt', 'mode': '0644'}`, and header `x-agentcube-session-id: <session_id>`\n\n#### Scenario: Download file with streaming\n- **GIVEN** `download_file(remote_path=\"/data/result.json\", local_path=\"./result.json\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the file is downloaded\n- **THEN** the system SHALL GET `api/files/data/result.json` (cleaned path) with `stream=True`, write response content to `./result.json`, and close response after writing\n\n#### Scenario: List files in directory\n- **GIVEN** `list_files(path=\"/home/user\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the request completes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL GET `api/files?path=/home/user` and return the JSON response\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient base URL construction\nThe system SHALL construct base URL from router URL, namespace, and agent name.\n\n#### Scenario: Base URL from router and agent metadata\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(router_url=\"http://router:9000\", namespace=\"default\", agent_name=\"my-agent\")` is initialized\n- **WHEN** the base URL is constructed\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `http://router:9000/v1/namespaces/default/agent-runtimes/my-agent/invocations/`\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient bootstrap session ID\nThe system SHALL bootstrap session ID by GETting the base invocation URL and reading `x-agentcube-session-id` header.\n\n#### Scenario: Bootstrap session ID from GET request\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is initialized without session_id\n- **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL GET `self.base_url` and extract the `x-agentcube-session-id` header from the response\n\n#### Scenario: Bootstrap fails with missing header\n- **GIVEN** the GET request to bootstrap succeeds but `x-agentcube-session-id` header is missing\n- **WHEN** the response is processed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message `Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id`\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient invoke with POST\nThe system SHALL POST JSON payloads to the base invocation URL with session header and Content-Type.\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke with JSON payload\n- **GIVEN** `invoke(session_id=\"session-abc\", payload={\"input\": \"data\"})` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** the system SHALL POST to `self.base_url` with headers `x-agentcube-session-id: session-abc` and `Content-Type: application/json`, and JSON body `{\"input\": \"data\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke with timeout tuple\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)` is initialized\n- **WHEN** `invoke(session_id=\"session-abc\", payload={}, timeout=None)` is called\n- **THEN** the request timeout SHALL be `(5.0, 120)`\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke without session ID raises error\n- **GIVEN** `invoke(session_id=\"\", payload={})` is called with falsy session_id\n- **WHEN** the method executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n\n### Requirement: HTTP session management with connection pooling\nThe system SHALL use `requests.Session` with `HTTPAdapter` for connection pooling on all HTTP clients.\n\n#### Scenario: Create session with default pool settings\n- **GIVEN** `create_session()` is called without arguments\n- **WHEN** the session is created\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create `requests.Session`, mount `HTTPAdapter` with `pool_connections=10` and `pool_maxsize=10` for both `http://` and `https://`, and return the session\n\n#### Scenario: Create session with custom pool settings\n- **GIVEN** `create_session(pool_connections=20, pool_maxsize=20)` is called\n- **WHEN** the session is created\n- **THEN** the system SHALL mount `HTTPAdapter` with the custom pool values\n\n#### Scenario: Closing sessions releases connections\n- **GIVEN** a client has an active `requests.Session`\n- **WHEN** `close()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `self.session.close()` to properly close the session and release connections\n\n### Requirement: Context manager support for HTTP clients\nThe system SHALL support context manager protocol via `__enter__` and `__exit__` for proper resource cleanup.\n\n#### Scenario: Control plane client context manager\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` is used in a `with` block\n- **WHEN** the block exits\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `close()` to close the HTTP session\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient context manager\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is used in a `with` block\n- **WHEN** the block exits\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `close()` to close the HTTP session\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient context manager\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is used in a `with` block\n- **WHEN** the block exits\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `close()` to close the HTTP session\n\n### Requirement: Exception hierarchy for HTTP operations\nThe system SHALL define `AgentCubeError` as base exception, with `SessionError` and `DataPlaneError` for HTTP client operations.\n\n#### Scenario: SessionError for control plane failures\n- **GIVEN** a control plane operation fails\n- **WHEN** the error is raised\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `SessionError` (subclass of `AgentCubeError`)\n\n#### Scenario: DataPlaneError for data plane failures\n- **GIVEN** a data plane operation fails\n- **WHEN** the error is raised\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `DataPlaneError` (subclass of `AgentCubeError`)\n\n### Requirement: Token file reading utility\nThe system SHALL provide `read_token_from_file` utility to read Kubernetes service account tokens.\n\n#### Scenario: Read existing token file\n- **GIVEN** `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` contains token content with newline\n- **WHEN** `read_token_from_file(\"/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token\")` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return the token content stripped of whitespace\n\n#### Scenario: Token file missing returns empty string\n- **GIVEN** the token file does not exist\n- **WHEN** `read_token_from_file(\"/nonexistent/token\")` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return empty string without raising exception\n\n### Requirement: Logger configuration utility\nThe system SHALL provide `get_logger` utility for consistent logger configuration.\n\n#### Scenario: Logger with default INFO level\n- **GIVEN** `get_logger(\"agentcube.client\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the logger is created\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return a `logging.Logger` instance with name `\"agentcube.client\"` and level `logging.INFO`\n\n#### Scenario: Logger with custom level\n- **GIVEN** `get_logger(\"agentcube.client\", level=logging.DEBUG)` is called\n- **WHEN** the logger is created\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return a logger with level set to `logging.DEBUG`\n\n## Acceptance Criteria Summary\n\n1. ✅ Client initialization resolves environment variables correctly\n2. ✅ Context manager protocol properly manages lifecycle\n3. ✅ Data plane failures trigger cleanup before re-raising\n4. ✅ Commands execute with proper timeout and error handling\n5. ✅ Code execution handles Python specially via file operations\n6. ✅ File operations (write, upload, download, list) work correctly\n7. ✅ HTTP sessions use connection pooling\n8. ✅ Logging configured with appropriate levels\n9. ✅ Session headers injected in all data plane requests\n10. ✅ Base URLs constructed correctly for data plane\n11. ✅ Control plane session create/delete work with 404 tolerance\n12. ✅ Verbose mode provides debug logging when enabled\n13. ✅ TTL and namespace parameters propagate correctly\n14. ✅ Optional metadata supported in session creation\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- `requests` library for HTTP client functionality\n- `PyJWT>=2.0.0` for JWT token handling (if needed)\n- `cryptography` for cryptographic operations (if needed)\n- Python >=3.10\n\n## References\n\n- Base Design: `python-sdk/design.md`\n- Base Specification: `python-sdk/spec.md`\n- AR: AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient","after":"# Delta Specification: AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n\n## AR Metadata\n- **AR ID**: AR-029\n- **Title**: SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n- **Module**: sdk-python\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Status**: Implementation Required\n\n## Purpose\nThis delta specification defines implementation requirements for the HTTP底层客户端 components in the AgentCube Python SDK, including `ControlPlaneClient`, `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, and `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`. It focuses on HTTP session management, connection pooling, timeout configuration, header management, and exception handling across all HTTP client implementations.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient initialization with environment variable resolution\nThe system SHALL resolve `base_url` from `workload_manager_url` parameter or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` environment variable, and resolve `auth_token` from parameter or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`.\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager URL from parameter\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\")` is called\n- **WHEN** initialization completes\n- **THEN** the client SHALL use `http://wm:8080` as `base_url` directly\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager URL from environment\n- **GIVEN** environment variable `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` is set to `http://wm-default:8080`\n- **WHEN** `ControlPlaneClient()` is called without `workload_manager_url`\n- **THEN** the client SHALL resolve `base_url` to `http://wm-default:8080`\n\n#### Scenario: Auth token from Kubernetes service account\n- **GIVEN** `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` contains valid JWT token\n- **WHEN** `ControlPlaneClient()` is called without `auth_token` parameter\n- **THEN** the client SHALL read and use the token from the file path via `read_token_from_file`\n\n#### Scenario: Service account token file missing\n- **GIVEN** `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` does not exist\n- **WHEN** `auth_token` is not provided and `read_token_from_file` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return empty string and no `Authorization` header will be set on the session\n\n### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient session creation via HTTP POST\nThe system SHALL create sessions by POSTing to `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with proper headers and JSON body.\n\n#### Scenario: Create session with all parameters\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(base_url=\"http://wm:8080\")` is initialized\n- **WHEN** `create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"dev\", ttl=1800, metadata={\"key\": \"value\"})` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL POST `http://wm:8080/v1/code-interpreter` with `Content-Type: application/json`, `Authorization: Bearer {token}` (if token present), and JSON body `{\"name\": \"test\", \"namespace\": \"dev\", \"ttl\": 1800, \"metadata\": {\"key\": \"value\"}}`\n\n#### Scenario: Create session returns session ID\n- **GIVEN** the control plane POST succeeds with response `{\"sessionId\": \"new-session-123\", ...}`\n- **WHEN** the response is parsed\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return `\"new-session-123\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Create session missing session ID in response\n- **GIVEN** the control plane POST succeeds but response JSON lacks `sessionId` field\n- **WHEN** the response is parsed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating missing `sessionId`\n\n### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient session deletion via HTTP DELETE with 404 tolerance\nThe system SHALL delete sessions by DELETEing to `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` with 404 treated as success.\n\n#### Scenario: Delete session success\n- **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session-123\")` is called and server returns 200 or 204\n- **WHEN** the response is processed\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`\n\n#### Scenario: Delete session 404 treated as success\n- **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session-404\")` is called and server returns 404\n- **WHEN** the response is received\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return `True` (session already deleted)\n\n#### Scenario: Delete session other failure\n- **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session-err\")` is called and server returns 500\n- **WHEN** the error occurs\n- **THEN** the method SHALL log the error and return `False`\n\n### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient timeout and connection pooling configuration\nThe system SHALL use configurable timeouts and connection pooling via `HTTPAdapter`.\n\n#### Scenario: Default timeout and pool settings\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient()` is initialized without timeout parameters\n- **WHEN** requests are made\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, and `pool_maxsize=10`\n\n#### Scenario: Custom timeout and pool settings\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(timeout=300, connect_timeout=10.0, pool_connections=20, pool_maxsize=20)` is initialized\n- **WHEN** requests are made\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use the custom values for timeouts and connection pooling\n\n#### Scenario: Timeout tuple applied to requests\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)` is initialized\n- **WHEN** any HTTP request is made\n- **THEN** the request timeout SHALL be `(5.0, 120)` (connect, read)\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient base URL construction\nThe system SHALL construct base URL from router URL, namespace, and CR name unless explicitly provided.\n\n#### Scenario: Base URL from router and metadata\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(router_url=\"http://router:9000\", namespace=\"default\", cr_name=\"my-interpreter\")` is initialized without `base_url`\n- **WHEN** the base URL is constructed\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `http://router:9000/v1/namespaces/default/code-interpreters/my-interpreter/invocations/`\n\n#### Scenario: Explicit base URL overrides construction\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(base_url=\"http://custom:8080/custom/path/\")` is provided\n- **WHEN** initialization completes\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `http://custom:8080/custom/path/` without any router-based construction\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient session header injection\nThe system SHALL inject `x-agentcube-session-id` header into all requests using lowercase header name.\n\n#### Scenario: Request includes session header\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(session_id=\"session-abc\")` is initialized\n- **WHEN** any `_request()` method call is made\n- **THEN** the request headers SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: session-abc`\n\n#### Scenario: Multipart upload includes session header\n- **GIVEN** `upload_file()` is called\n- **WHEN** the multipart POST is prepared\n- **THEN** the request SHALL explicitly set `x-agentcube-session-id` header alongside the multipart files and data\n\n#### Scenario: JSON request includes session header\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command()` is called with a JSON body\n- **WHEN** the POST request is sent\n- **THEN** the request SHALL include both `Content-Type: application/json` and `x-agentcube-session-id: <session_id>` headers\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient execute command with timeout buffer\nThe system SHALL POST to `api/execute` with JSON body and apply read timeout buffer to avoid premature ReadTimeout.\n\n#### Scenario: Execute command with default timeout\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"echo hello\")` is called without timeout parameter\n- **WHEN** the request is prepared\n- **THEN** the body SHALL be `{\"command\": [\"echo\", \"hello\"], \"timeout\": \"120s\"}` and HTTP read timeout SHALL be `122.0` seconds (120 + 2.0 buffer)\n\n#### Scenario: Execute command with custom timeout\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"sleep 10\", timeout=30.0)` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is prepared\n- **THEN** the body SHALL include `timeout: \"30s\"` and the HTTP read timeout SHALL be `32.0` seconds (30 + 2.0 buffer)\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient file operations\nThe system SHALL support write, upload, download, and list file operations with proper encoding and headers.\n\n#### Scenario: Write file with base64 encoding\n- **GIVEN** `write_file(content=\"hello world\", remote_path=\"/tmp/test.txt\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** the system SHALL POST to `api/files` with JSON `{\"content\": \"<base64>\", \"path\": \"/tmp/test.txt\", \"mode\": \"0644\"}` where content is base64-encoded\n\n#### Scenario: Upload file via multipart\n- **GIVEN** `upload_file(local_path=\"/local/file.txt\", remote_path=\"/remote/file.txt\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the multipart request is sent\n- **THEN** the system SHALL POST to `api/files` with `files={'file': open('/local/file.txt', 'rb')}`, `data={'path': '/remote/file.txt', 'mode': '0644'}`, and header `x-agentcube-session-id: <session_id>`\n\n#### Scenario: Download file with streaming\n- **GIVEN** `download_file(remote_path=\"/data/result.json\", local_path=\"./result.json\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the file is downloaded\n- **THEN** the system SHALL GET `api/files/data/result.json` (cleaned path) with `stream=True`, write response content to `./result.json`, and close response after writing\n\n#### Scenario: List files in directory\n- **GIVEN** `list_files(path=\"/home/user\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the request completes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL GET `api/files?path=/home/user` and return the JSON response\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient base URL construction\nThe system SHALL construct base URL from router URL, namespace, and agent name.\n\n#### Scenario: Base URL from router and agent metadata\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(router_url=\"http://router:9000\", namespace=\"default\", agent_name=\"my-agent\")` is initialized\n- **WHEN** the base URL is constructed\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `http://router:9000/v1/namespaces/default/agent-runtimes/my-agent/invocations/`\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient bootstrap session ID\nThe system SHALL bootstrap session ID by GETting the base invocation URL and reading `x-agentcube-session-id` header.\n\n#### Scenario: Bootstrap session ID from GET request\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is initialized without session_id\n- **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL GET `self.base_url` and extract the `x-agentcube-session-id` header from the response\n\n#### Scenario: Bootstrap fails with missing header\n- **GIVEN** the GET request to bootstrap succeeds but `x-agentcube-session-id` header is missing\n- **WHEN** the response is processed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message `Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id`\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient invoke with POST\nThe system SHALL POST JSON payloads to the base invocation URL with session header and Content-Type.\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke with JSON payload\n- **GIVEN** `invoke(session_id=\"session-abc\", payload={\"input\": \"data\"})` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** the system SHALL POST to `self.base_url` with headers `x-agentcube-session-id: session-abc` and `Content-Type: application/json`, and JSON body `{\"input\": \"data\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke with timeout tuple\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)` is initialized\n- **WHEN** `invoke(session_id=\"session-abc\", payload={}, timeout=None)` is called\n- **THEN** the request timeout SHALL be `(5.0, 120)`\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke without session ID raises error\n- **GIVEN** `invoke(session_id=\"\", payload={})` is called with falsy session_id\n- **WHEN** the method executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n\n### Requirement: HTTP session management with connection pooling\nThe system SHALL use `requests.Session` with `HTTPAdapter` for connection pooling on all HTTP clients.\n\n#### Scenario: Create session with default pool settings\n- **GIVEN** `create_session()` is called without arguments\n- **WHEN** the session is created\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create `requests.Session`, mount `HTTPAdapter` with `pool_connections=10` and `pool_maxsize=10` for both `http://` and `https://`, and return the session\n\n#### Scenario: Create session with custom pool settings\n- **GIVEN** `create_session(pool_connections=20, pool_maxsize=20)` is called\n- **WHEN** the session is created\n- **THEN** the system SHALL mount `HTTPAdapter` with the custom pool values\n\n#### Scenario: Closing sessions releases connections\n- **GIVEN** a client has an active `requests.Session`\n- **WHEN** `close()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `self.session.close()` to properly close the session and release connections\n\n### Requirement: Context manager support for HTTP clients\nThe system SHALL support context manager protocol via `__enter__` and `__exit__` for proper resource cleanup.\n\n#### Scenario: Control plane client context manager\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` is used in a `with` block\n- **WHEN** the block exits\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `close()` to close the HTTP session\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient context manager\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is used in a `with` block\n- **WHEN** the block exits\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `close()` to close the HTTP session\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient context manager\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is used in a `with` block\n- **WHEN** the block exits\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `close()` to close the HTTP session\n\n### Requirement: Exception hierarchy for HTTP operations\nThe system SHALL define `AgentCubeError` as base exception, with `SessionError` and `DataPlaneError` for HTTP client operations.\n\n#### Scenario: SessionError for control plane failures\n- **GIVEN** a control plane operation fails\n- **WHEN** the error is raised\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `SessionError` (subclass of `AgentCubeError`)\n\n#### Scenario: DataPlaneError for data plane failures\n- **GIVEN** a data plane operation fails\n- **WHEN** the error is raised\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `DataPlaneError` (subclass of `AgentCubeError`)\n\n### Requirement: Token file reading utility\nThe system SHALL provide `read_token_from_file` utility to read Kubernetes service account tokens.\n\n#### Scenario: Read existing token file\n- **GIVEN** `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` contains token content with newline\n- **WHEN** `read_token_from_file(\"/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token\")` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return the token content stripped of whitespace\n\n#### Scenario: Token file missing returns empty string\n- **GIVEN** the token file does not exist\n- **WHEN** `read_token_from_file(\"/nonexistent/token\")` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return empty string without raising exception\n\n### Requirement: Logger configuration utility\nThe system SHALL provide `get_logger` utility for consistent logger configuration.\n\n#### Scenario: Logger with default INFO level\n- **GIVEN** `get_logger(\"agentcube.client\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the logger is created\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return a `logging.Logger` instance with name `\"agentcube.client\"` and level `logging.INFO`\n\n#### Scenario: Logger with custom level\n- **GIVEN** `get_logger(\"agentcube.client\", level=logging.DEBUG)` is called\n- **WHEN** the logger is created\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return a logger with level set to `logging.DEBUG`\n\n## Acceptance Criteria Summary\n\n1. ✅ ControlPlaneClient resolves environment variables for base_url and auth_token\n2. ✅ ControlPlaneClient creates sessions via POST with proper headers and JSON body\n3. ✅ ControlPlaneClient deletes sessions via DELETE with 404 tolerance\n4. ✅ ControlPlaneClient uses configurable timeouts and connection pooling\n5. ✅ CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient constructs base URL from router URL, namespace, and CR name\n6. ✅ CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient injects x-agentcube-session-id header in all requests\n7. ✅ CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient executes commands with timeout buffer to avoid ReadTimeout\n8. ✅ CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient supports write, upload, download, and list file operations\n9. ✅ AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient constructs base URL from router URL, namespace, and agent name\n10. ✅ AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient bootstraps session ID via GET request\n11. ✅ AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient invokes workloads via POST with JSON payload\n12. ✅ HTTP session management uses requests.Session with HTTPAdapter for connection pooling\n13. ✅ Context manager support ensures proper resource cleanup\n14. ✅ Exception hierarchy defines AgentCubeError, SessionError, and DataPlaneError\n15. ✅ Token file reading utility reads Kubernetes service account tokens\n16. ✅ Logger configuration utility provides consistent logger setup\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- `requests` library for HTTP client functionality\n- `PyJWT>=2.0.0` for JWT token handling (if needed)\n- `cryptography` for cryptographic operations (if needed)\n- Python >=3.10\n\n## References\n\n- Base Design: `python-sdk/design.md`\n- Base Specification: `python-sdk/spec.md`\n- AR: AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端","additions":17,"deletions":15},"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775879464072,"end":1775879464091}}}}
